1
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,800
(MICHAEL) My dear children,

2
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:55,000
it is now better than several years
since I moved to New York

3
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:59,300
and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.

4
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,600
I hope you will come to this ceremony
of Papal honours,

5
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:06,200
given for my charitable work.

6
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:11,700
The only wealth in this world is children.

7
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,000
More than all the money
and power on Earth.

8
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:18,300
You are my treasure.

9
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:22,100
Anthony and Mary,

10
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:26,900
although I entrusted your education to
your mother for your own best interest,

11
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:33,200
I look forward to seeing you, and to
a new period of harmony in our lives.

12
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:39,200
Perhaps you might prevail upon your
mother to come to this celebration,

13
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:44,700
and that from time to time, we can all
see each other at family functions.

14
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:50,400
Anyway, I remain your loving father.

15
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,100
(ARCHBISHOP) Adjutorium nostrum

16
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:59,500
in nomine Domine.

17
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:04,000
(PRIESTS) Qui fecit caelum et terram.

18
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:08,200
Dominus vobiscum.

19
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:13,000
(PRIESTS) Et cum spiritu tuo.

20
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,300
(ARCHBISHOP) Oremus.

21
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:20,100
(ARCHBISHOP) Paulus Sextus,
Pontifex Maximus...

22
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,400
(FREDO) Hail Mary, full of grace...

23
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,400
(ARCHBISHOP)... precibus nobi
adhibit libenti...

24
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,800
(FREDO)
...blessed art thou amongst women...

25
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,000
(ARCHBISHOP)... animo concedente...

26
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:34,100
...and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

27
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:38,100
Holy Mary, mother of God,
pray for us sinners...

28
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:42,100
(ARCHBISHOP)... te Michael Corleone...

29
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,500
(GUNSHOT)

30
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:08,900
Almighty God, bless the insignia
of Saint Sebastian the Martyr,

31
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:15,300
that it may contribute to the sacredness
of him to whom it is given.

32
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:35,100
Do you, Michael, promise to be faithful
to the noble purposes of this Order,

33
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:40,000
to have a special care for the poor,
the needy and those who are ill?

34
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,100
I do so promise.

35
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,300
In nomine Patris,

36
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:48,400
Filii et Spiritu Sancti.

37
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:55,700
(ARCHBISHOP CONTINUES BLESSING)

38
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:00,500
May the blessing of Almighty God,

39
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:05,500
Father, Son and Holy Spirit

40
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:11,000
descend upon you
and remain with you forever.

41
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,700
(CHOIR SINGS)

42
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,500
(SINGS LIVELY SICILIAN SONG)

43
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:48,100
Vincent, our name is not on the list.

44
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:53,000
Write it in. Mancini. M-A-N-C-l-N-I.

45
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:58,100
- Problem?
- My name isn't on the list.

46
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:03,000
- Then you have to leave immediately.
- You want to dance with me?

47
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,900
Joe, it's Vinnie. These are our guests.

48
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,900
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, sir.

49
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,300
Welcome to the party.

50
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,600
(LIVELY SINGING CONTINUES)

51
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,900
(HE SINGS A LINE... )

52
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,000
(MUSIC STOPS)

53
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,200
(SONG ENDS, APPLAUSE)

54
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:08,000
- It's good to see you.
- Good to see you. This is my husband.

55
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:10,900
- Sit down.
- My son, Anthony.

56
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:16,500
The Order of Saint Sebastian is one of
the highest honours the Church awards.

57
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,900
It was first granted by Pope...

58
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:22,500
What about Mr Corleone's connections
with gambling?

59
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,900
The press kits have...

60
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,800
- And involvement with the underworld?
- Cut the crap.

61
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:32,100
The Pope, the Holy Father himself,

62
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:36,900
has today blessed Michael Corleone.
Do you know better than the Pope?

63
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:40,900
Vincent! She loves you.

64
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:42,900
Yeah?

65
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,200
I love you too.

66
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:57,600
Hi, Vincent. I remember you.

67
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:03,100
- From where?
- The last party we were at together.

68
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:07,500
- Did you come to the club?
- No, it was a wedding.

69
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,800
I was eight and you were 15.

70
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:15,100
I had many girlfriends when I was 15.

71
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,600
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially them.

72
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,900
Where's Mary?

73
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:26,600
Would somebody please hail Mary?
Excuse me, Your Excellency.

74
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:31,300
You haven't kissed me hello yet.
Relatives always kiss.

75
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:35,100
- Now we're related?
- I'm your little cousin.

76
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:46,000
- Who's your father?
- I'll give you a hint.

77
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,800
He's Italian.

78
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:52,700
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

79
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:56,500
Remember to keep your voice low.

80
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:59,400
And smile. Don't forget to smile.

81
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:23,300
The honorary chairman
of the Vito Corleone Foundation:

82
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,200
My daughter, Mary Corleone.

83
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,800
Thanks.

84
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:43,800
I think I inherited my father's love
for speechmaking. Here it goes.

85
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:49,600
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps
the poor in every country,

86
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:54,400
gives grants to artists,
funds medical research,

87
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:59,300
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

88
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,700
Archbishop Gilday,

89
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:08,200
here is 100 million dollars for the poor
of Sicily, in the name of Vito Corleone.

90
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,700
Don't spend it all in one place.

91
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:34,600
Mary, I'm so proud of you.

92
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,100
Michael...

93
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:46,600
You've done a wonderful thing for Sicily.

94
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,700
Let's hope that the money gets
to the people who need it.

95
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,400
Amen.

96
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,400
...the most important part:
Johnny Fontane!

97
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:08,800
Thank you very much.
I'm happy to be here.

98
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:14,200
I would like you to join me in honouring
Commendatore Michael Corleone.

99
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,100
I have something special
for our godfather.

100
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:26,800
I happen to know his favourite song.
Michael, where are you going?

101
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:31,200
I'm off to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

102
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,700
Your favourite song: "Salsiccia's Own".

103
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,400
I'm having a salsiccia sandwich.
I'll be back.

104
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:48,100
# A rose must remain
With the sun and the rain

105
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:52,700
# Or its lovely promise
won't come true

106
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,700
# To each his own... #

107
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:00,100
(SONG CONTINUES IN BACKGROUND)

108
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,500
Hello, Kay.

109
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:27,400
Congratulations, Michael.
That's quite an honour.

110
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:30,600
But a little expensive, wouldn't you say?

111
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:36,200
- Cake?
- No, thank you.

112
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:43,500
(HE SINGS IN ITALIAN)

113
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:53,100
- It's been a long time, hasn't it?
- Yeah.

114
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,800
- Eight years.
- Yeah.

115
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,300
You look wonderful.

116
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:06,300
Your son has something he wants to
talk to you about. I came here for him.

117
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:21,600
# If a flame has to grow
There must be a glow

118
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:26,300
# To open each door there's a key

119
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:31,400
# I need you, I know
I can't let you go... #

120
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:46,500
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- He wants his life to be in music.

121
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:52,400
Music is great, I love music.
But he should finish what he started.

122
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,300
Anthony...

123
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:57,600
- I'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

124
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,400
- Professional singer?
- Right.

125
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,900
What happens if you fail?

126
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:07,300
- I won't fail.
- Men always believe that.

127
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:11,300
A law degree
is like taking out insurance.

128
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:15,800
- After that you can work for me...
- I will never work for you.

129
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:19,400
I have bad memories.

130
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:22,800
Every family has bad memories.

131
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:30,700
I'll always be your son, but won't have
anything to do with your business.

132
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:37,400
Anthony... finish the law degree.

133
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,300
No.

134
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:01,200
Well, that he got from you. That "no".

135
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:09,400
- You could've helped me convince him.
- Convince him of what?

136
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,900
Of what?

137
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:16,900
He throws his life away.
He throws greatness away.

138
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:20,100
This is greatness?

139
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:25,200
Now that you're so respectable,
you're more dangerous than ever.

140
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:29,800
I preferred you when you were
just a common Mafia hood.

141
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,500
OK.

142
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,700
- Can we talk common sense here?
- All right.

143
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:46,600
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

144
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,900
- What did you come here for?
- To protect my son.

145
00:16:56,300 --> 00:17:01,300
Not to see you disguised by your
church. That was a shameful ceremony.

146
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:08,500
I spent my life protecting my son.

147
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:12,300
I spent my life protecting my family!

148
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:15,300
Let's be reasonable, OK?

149
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:20,500
That's your big thing,
isn't it, Michael? Reason.

150
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:25,100
- Backed up by murder.
- Oh, God.

151
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:29,900
- You hate me. You hate me.
- No.

152
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:32,300
I don't hate you.

153
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:36,200
I dread you.

154
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:45,200
I did what I could, Kay, to protect all
of you from the horrors of this world.

155
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:49,500
But you became my horror.

156
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:02,500
The children still love you, though.
Especially Mary.

157
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,400
That's something.

158
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:13,400
We can build on that. For their sake.

159
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,700
Let's try.

160
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:24,000
Only if you let Tony go free to have
his own life, away from you.

161
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:34,100
I'll let Tony go.

162
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,700
Thank you.

163
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,200
- Hi.
- Hi.

164
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:21,100
You could hurt somebody with those.
Let me show you around.

165
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,800
Can you get me an interview
with Corleone?

166
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:29,000
No. I'm a relative, but I can't do that.
What else can I do for you?

167
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:32,500
- Handsome, but useless.
- Oh, yeah?

168
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,700
- That's OK, I'll gamble.
- Do you like to gamble?

169
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:39,600
Let's go to Atlantic City.
I'll show you how to gamble.

170
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:44,000
- How will I know what numbers to bet?
- Do I look like a loser?

171
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:46,200
Well...

172
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,500
Spooky-looking guy there.

173
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:55,800
- What's a guy like that doing here?
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

174
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,700
- You know him?
- Yeah, I do.

175
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:03,700
His name is Anthony Squigilaro.
They call him "The Ant".

176
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:07,000
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

177
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,100
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

178
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,600
Don Altobello.

179
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:22,300
- I've come to pay my respects.
- Grazie.

180
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:28,100
You honour my father's friendship.

181
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:31,700
Where is my god-daughter?

182
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:34,700
- Constanza!
- Don Altobello.

183
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:39,600
It was not so long ago
that I held you in these old hands.

184
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,000
Michael...

185
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,400
(SICILIAN)

186
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:52,600
Michael, I've lost all the venom,
all the juice of youth.

187
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:58,500
I've lost the lust for women,
and now my mind is clear.

188
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:05,500
My duty to God is clear.
I have a special favour to ask of you.

189
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:14,000
Can I attach my name
to the Vito Corleone Foundation,

190
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:19,800
so that you and I can be joined
in name and spirit?

191
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:26,700
- One million dollars.
- Oh, my!

192
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:33,500
- Godfather.
- Don Altobello, you have such a heart.

193
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:40,800
Come, let's go and sample
some of that old vino.

194
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:51,000
The Vatican knows nothing
about these shareholders.

195
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:52,500
Good.

196
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:57,500
I have a tendency to worry. We've
increased our position substantially.

197
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:03,000
- Naturally, I worry.
- Stop worrying, we have an agreement.

198
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:07,200
Good. How do you think
I got this grey hair?

199
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:11,800
Two seconds... Thank you for your
contribution to the swimming-pool.

200
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:16,200
We need your help on Sam Wallace's
candidacy for judgeship.

201
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:18,800
- We can always use a good judge.
- Thanks.

202
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,600
Andrew!

203
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:24,800
My godson Andrew Hagen.
My brother Tom's eldest boy.

204
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:29,000
He's been assistant
to Bishop Breelan for three years.

205
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:33,400
- Hopes to be assigned to the Vatican.
- Rome needs fine young priests.

206
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:36,900
His mother Theresa Hagen,
Bishop Gilday.

207
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,100
Honoured to meet you.

208
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:42,500
Mr Corleone. Hi. Grace Hamilton.

209
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:48,300
Vincent Mancini promised to tell you
about me, that maybe you'd see me.

210
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,800
- Did Vincent Mancini call about her?
- No.

211
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,200
- You promised to stay out there, twice.
- I know.

212
00:22:57,500 --> 00:23:01,100
Joey Zasa showed up.
He's waiting in the lobby.

213
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:05,300
He wants to personally
congratulate you. Show his respect.

214
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:10,600
- Do I have to see him?
- He says you're his patron.

215
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,300
Hey, Vinnie!

216
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,700
- Who's your favourite aunt?
- You are.

217
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:25,800
Today I'll talk to Michael
about your little problem.

218
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:30,200
If you'd warned me,
I would have worn a better suit.

219
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:34,400
The Meucci Association
has elected you

220
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:37,300
Italian-American Man of the Year.

221
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:41,000
Meucci...

222
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:45,800
Who's Meucci?

223
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:51,600
The Italian-American who invented
the telephone, one year before Bell.

224
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:58,900
And this is the reason
you've come today?

225
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:08,400
I...

226
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:13,000
I've got a stone in my shoe.

227
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:17,400
A two-bit punk who works for me.

228
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:21,600
The one who thinks he's related to you.

229
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,300
A bastard.

230
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:33,200
He's here. Vincent Mancini.
He's at the party.

231
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:38,300
Bring him in.

232
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:42,600
I think it's good that we talk.

233
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:45,000
No, grazie.

234
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:49,100
I have a problem...

235
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:55,400
...and I want to find out if it is
my problem or your problem.

236
00:24:55,800 --> 00:25:01,300
Your business is your business. I have
no interests or percentages from it.

237
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:05,600
Good. Then it's my problem.

238
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:13,700
Michael, you know Vincent Mancini.
Sonny's boy.

239
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:19,100
- How are you, Mr Corleone?
- How are you?

240
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:22,900
- Good. How are you? Good party.
- You like it?

241
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:26,400
- Yes, I had to sneak in.
- You're dressed for it.

242
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:35,600
So, what's the trouble
between you and Mr Joe Zasa?

243
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:41,500
- Just trouble. I'll take care of it.
- That's foolish of you.

244
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:47,200
Foolish of me? It's a little foolish
of this guy, don't you think? Right?

245
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:52,000
- Right?!
- Temper like his father...

246
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:54,500
Vincent...

247
00:25:55,600 --> 00:26:00,700
Mr Joe Zasa now owns what used to
be the Corleone business in New York.

248
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:05,000
Out of kindness,
he gave you a job in his family.

249
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:08,100
You took it against my advice.

250
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:13,100
