they would be a dog.

270
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:53,700
- My interests don't conflict with his.
- You don't know how much they do.

271
00:27:54,100 --> 00:27:55,700
Quiet, Vincent.

272
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,000
He needs your support!

273
00:27:58,300 --> 00:28:01,900
Don't let me work for this guy,
let me work for you.

274
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:07,900
As what? Tough guy? I don't need
tough guys. I need more lawyers.

275
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:16,400
Since we have no conflicts or debts,
I accept your tribute. I wish you well.

276
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:22,900
Vincent, make your peace
with Mr Joe Zasa. Go on.

277
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:35,900
Bastardo...

278
00:28:41,100 --> 00:28:43,900
Vinnie, what's the matter with you?!

279
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,400
Get him out of here.

280
00:28:47,700 --> 00:28:49,700
Jesus Christ...

281
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:54,000
- I told Connie this wasn't the right time.
- Close it.

282
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:57,800
I know you're into Wall Street,
but you're still the final word.

283
00:28:58,200 --> 00:29:00,900
I want to protect you from these guys.
Your lawyers can't.

284
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:04,700
- But you can?
- Yeah, I can do that.

285
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:07,400
Why should I be afraid of Zasa?

286
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:10,400
You stop him from rising
in the Commission.

287
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:14,000
I say we make him dead.
Give me the order, I'll do it.

288
00:29:14,300 --> 00:29:16,300
- You'll do it?
- Yeah.

289
00:29:20,500 --> 00:29:25,300
Maybe you should come with me
for a few weeks. See what happens.

290
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:28,700
- OK.
- See if you learn.

291
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:32,900
And we'll talk about your future.

292
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:36,200
I won't let you down.

293
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:44,600
It's about ready.

294
00:29:50,300 --> 00:29:51,600
What happened?

295
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:55,600
If I'm in a room with Zasa,
what happens? I bit his ear off.

296
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:58,700
Here we go. Watch the card.

297
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,500
Hold it!

298
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,700
- Vincent...
- Yeah.

299
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,400
Take the picture with us.

300
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:18,800
Nice jacket.

301
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:22,600
Closer to the centre, sir.

302
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:27,300
Smile!

303
00:30:46,700 --> 00:30:51,700
Godfather, this is the cake for you
and your family from Enzo the baker.

304
00:30:52,500 --> 00:30:54,800
Do you want to do it?

305
00:31:40,700 --> 00:31:43,400
Cent'anni! Cent'anni!

306
00:32:43,300 --> 00:32:46,500
- Vincent?
- What do you want, sweetheart?

307
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:50,900
Do you love me?

308
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:55,900
- Come on, go to bed.
- Come on, say it.

309
00:32:56,300 --> 00:32:58,500
I love you.

310
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:00,900
I love you, too.

311
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,900
(SLIGHT SOUND)

312
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:05,300
You've got a cat?

313
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:14,800
Go get us some water, I'm thirsty.
Come on.

314
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,600
Come on.

315
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:27,500
Well, I guess I know my place.

316
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:31,600
I can't believe I'm actually doing this.

317
00:33:31,900 --> 00:33:35,900
"Get me water, bake me a cake"...
What happened to "please"?

318
00:34:23,900 --> 00:34:26,600
(VINCENT)
Good boy, Sackface. Go for a walk.

319
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:38,400
- Let her go.
- Cut her throat, man.

320
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:44,100
- What did you say?
- Cut her fucking throat.

321
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:50,200
- OK, chief...
- Drop your gun or he'll cut her throat.

322
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:54,200
I hardly know her, so cut her.
What the fuck do I care?

323
00:34:56,400 --> 00:35:00,000
You've got no choice. She'll be dead.

324
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:04,400
If you do, I'll kill you both.
Give up that knife, I'll let you go.

325
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:06,900
Cut her throat! Right now!

326
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:12,900
I'll do something that'll convince you.
Don't get frightened. Just watch me.

327
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:19,600
Oh, shit!

328
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:24,000
Drop the knife. Drop it!

329
00:35:24,300 --> 00:35:30,000
Good boy. Sit down, I want to talk
to you. It was a wise choice. Sit down.

330
00:35:31,100 --> 00:35:33,100
Lose the mask.

331
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,300
Relax, have a smoke. You smoke?

332
00:35:41,100 --> 00:35:44,100
Whose idea was this? Who sent you?

333
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:47,300
Tell me who sent you.

334
00:35:49,500 --> 00:35:52,200
- No one.
- Did you take a look at this guy?

335
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,700
- Yeah.
- Who sent you?

336
00:35:57,500 --> 00:35:59,700
It was Joey Zasa.

337
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:16,800
Are you OK?

338
00:36:19,100 --> 00:36:22,100
- You were going to let them kill me!
- No, I wasn't...

339
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:25,600
You pig! You sick fuck!

340
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:30,900
You wanted gambling. That's gambling.
Call the police.

341
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:39,300
- You killed the other guy too?
- He went for my gun.

342
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:43,100
It was self-defence.
Go ahead, call the police.

343
00:36:44,100 --> 00:36:46,100
- No, no...
- I'm taking pictures.

344
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:48,600
No pictures.

345
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:51,200
You had a gun!

346
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:56,400
They only had a knife. You could have
handed them over to the police.

347
00:36:56,700 --> 00:37:00,500
Zasa sent them.
I just sent him a message.

348
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:06,400
- Now he has to send you one back.
- Is Zasa going to send me one back?

349
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:09,500
He did the right thing.
He got Zasa's name!

350
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:14,800
What has Joey Zasa to do
with anything? Joey Zasa is a pazzo.

351
00:37:17,100 --> 00:37:19,800
All right. You are what you are.

352
00:37:20,300 --> 00:37:23,200
It's your nature. Stay close to me.

353
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:27,200
Don't do anything. Keep your mouth
shut and your eyes open.

354
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:30,600
- And you do what I tell you.
- I understand.

355
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:34,600
- I have problems with the Commission.
- I know.

356
00:37:34,900 --> 00:37:39,500
- You don't make them easier.
- It wasn't my idea that this happened.

357
00:37:39,900 --> 00:37:42,700
- Get out of here.
- Michael...

358
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,000
Yes?

359
00:37:45,500 --> 00:37:50,100
- Now they'll fear you.
- Maybe they should fear you.

360
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:57,000
- B.J., what's up?
- The Archbishop just called back.

361
00:37:57,400 --> 00:38:00,300
We've arranged some amazing things.

362
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:05,300
The publicity is phenomenal. You're
the new Rockefeller. A philanthropist.

363
00:38:06,700 --> 00:38:10,400
- Sign here, please.
- Times do change, don't they?

364
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:15,600
My father hated foundations.
He loved doing it by himself.

365
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:19,200
Man to man. But we're different.

366
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:24,100
No different than any large corporation.
We control a lot of money with little.

367
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:29,100
Minimise taxes.
With no government control.

368
00:38:38,100 --> 00:38:41,400
- Godfather.
- Andrew.

369
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:47,600
- Off to Rome...
- I wanted to thank you for everything.

370
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:51,000
- Do you want some breakfast?
- Thanks, I can't.

371
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:55,100
- How's your Italian?
- Devo fare un po' di pratica.

372
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:58,700
- His father was a great lawyer.
- I know.

373
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:03,500
Didn't live to see him ordained. I did.
Did you ever see one of those?

374
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:07,300
Beautiful. I was so proud.
Let me walk you out.

375
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:11,600
If you hear any rumours in the Vatican,
let me know.

376
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,600
No, Andrew has the true faith.

377
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:25,400
Don Corleone,

378
00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:30,100
I need your help. And not just
to light a little candle.

379
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:38,200
My gift was to be able to persuade
people to give to the Holy Church.

380
00:39:39,300 --> 00:39:44,000
Then Rome decides to put me
in charge of the Vatican Bank...

381
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:49,000
...but I was never a true banker.

382
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:56,300
Mea culpa. I trusted my friends.

383
00:39:57,500 --> 00:39:59,800
Friendship and money...

384
00:40:00,700 --> 00:40:02,400
Oil and water...

385
00:40:02,700 --> 00:40:04,300
Indeed.

386
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:11,200
But these "friends" used the good name
of the Church to feed their greed.

387
00:40:12,500 --> 00:40:15,100
If money was lost...

388
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:18,800
...then I am to blame.

389
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:25,200
If only prayer could pay off
our 700 million dollar deficit.

390
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:29,700
769 million...

391
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:40,400
The Church owns 25 percent
of a large corporation: Lmmobiliare.

392
00:40:41,500 --> 00:40:43,500
You know the one I mean?

393
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:48,800
Largest landlord on Earth.
Real estate worth six billion dollars.

394
00:40:50,700 --> 00:40:52,700
That's true.

395
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:56,900
And the Vatican vote
is necessary for control.

396
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:02,400
No, you're mistaken.

397
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:07,000
This isn't a question of one person
deciding, one deciding vote.

398
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:13,100
This is like any other company.
We have directors and very old rules.

399
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:18,700
The Pope himself
would have to approve you.

400
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,200
We've sold the casinos.

401
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:30,600
All businesses having to do
with gambling.

402
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:36,500
We have no interests or investments
in anything illegitimate.

403
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:44,300
The Corleones are prepared to deposit
500 million dollars in the Vatican Bank

404
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:47,700
when Mr Corleone receives majority
control at lmmobiliare.

405
00:41:47,900 --> 00:41:53,200
Immobiliare could be something new.
A European conglomerate.

406
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:58,700
Few families have control
of such a company.

407
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:04,700
It seems that, in today's world,

408
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:10,000
the power to absolve debt is greater
than the power of forgiveness.

409
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:13,500
600 million dollars.

410
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:22,100
Don't overestimate
the power of forgiveness.

411
00:42:23,700 --> 00:42:25,600
Don Corleone,

412
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:30,700
this deal with lmmobiliare can make you
one of the richest men in the world.

413
00:42:31,100 --> 00:42:36,400
Your whole past history, and the history
of your family, would be washed away.

414
00:42:40,500 --> 00:42:43,000
600 million.

415
00:42:58,100 --> 00:43:02,900
The motion under discussion
relates to Corleone Group's proposal

416
00:43:03,300 --> 00:43:08,700
to acquire 100,000,000 newly-issued
Class A voting shares.

417
00:43:10,500 --> 00:43:17,000
...Corleone capital invested directly
into International lmmobiliare,

418
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:21,200
an old and respected
European company.

419
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:26,600
Mr Corleone has an ambitious programme
to expand this real estate company

420
00:43:27,100 --> 00:43:30,000
into an international conglomerate...

421
00:43:33,500 --> 00:43:38,300
...threatened by Eastern techniques
of efficiency and focus and unlimited...

422
00:43:38,700 --> 00:43:41,500
Mr Corleone, excuse me.

423
00:43:41,900 --> 00:43:45,400
Didn't you recently deposit 200 million
in the Vatican Bank,

424
00:43:45,700 --> 00:43:48,500
which is affiliated with lmmobiliare?

425
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,300
True. Why not?

426
00:43:50,500 --> 00:43:55,800
Wasn't there any questioning about
the timing on this particular deposit?

427
00:43:56,800 --> 00:43:59,300
Mr Chairman, if I may?

428
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:05,100
The Vito Andolini Corleone Foundation,
of which Mary Corleone is chairman,

429
00:44:05,500 --> 00:44:08,700
has made an endowment
of 100 million dollars.

430
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:13,100
The money comes from his own family
and will be administered by the Vatican.

431
00:44:13,500 --> 00:44:16,000
Does that answer your question?

432
00:44:16,300 --> 00:44:22,400
I have always believed that helping your
fellow man is profitable in every sense,

433
00:44:22,700 --> 00:44:25,200
personally and bottom line.

434
00:44:25,700 --> 00:44:31,100
My fellow shareholders, if Europe
and America can learn to co-operate,

435
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:35,300
if we can learn to pool our wealth,
share our markets,

436
00:44:35,700 --> 00:44:40,500
we can defeat any competition
anywhere in the world.

437
00:44:41,300 --> 00:44:43,900
Thank you for your time.

438
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:48,600
I hope that you will look favourably
on my proposal. Thank you.

439
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:57,200
Let me have this microphone here.

440
00:44:57,600 --> 00:45:02,700
Will we let a criminal run our company?
He's got the map of Sicily on his face!

441
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:04,600
Order!

442
00:45:04,700 --> 00:45:07,600
He's either a Catholic or a mafioso...

443
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:14,000
The Hamilton Investors Group
cannot support this proposal.

444
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:16,100
Your Excellency...

445
00:45:17,300 --> 00:45:18,800
Mr Chairman...

446
00:45:19,600 --> 00:45:25,600
...the Vatican Bank feels
that International lmmobiliare...

447
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:31,700
...will be safe in Mr Corleone's hands.

448
00:45:32,100 --> 00:45:36,900
...subject to audit and final ratification,
which must take place in Rome.

449
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:41,000
Please join me in welcoming
Mr Michael Corleone.

450
00:45:51,100 --> 00:45:52,900
Dad?

451
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:58,900
Tony says that I'm a front
for the foundation.

452
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:03,800
That you're using me to pull the strings.

453
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:07,100
- To get the money where you want it.
- Please!

454
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:10,400
- To shine up your public image.
- Mary!

455
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:15,400
Mary, this is real.
This foundation is real.

456
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:22,700
I wanted Anthony to be part of it.
I thought you would be together on this.

457
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:27,400
I won't interfere.
I'll help, but only if you ask.

458
00:46:27,600 --> 00:46:30,200
What is this really for?

459
00:46:30,600 --> 00:46:35,200
Why are you doing this?
Why am I doing this?

460
00:46:35,600 --> 00:46:40,500
I'm doing this for my children.
You're doing it for your children too.

461
00:46:41,100 --> 00:46:44,200
This foundation is supposed
to help all people?

462
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:45,900
That's the purpose.

463
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:51,400
This is legitimate.
Mary, I swear, this is legitimate.

464
00:46:55,700 --> 00:46:59,100
Dad, I want this to bring me
closer to you.

465
00:47:06,900 --> 00:47:11,100
I would burn in hell to keep you safe.

466
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:27,800
Go in the other car. I'll ride with Michael.

467
00:47:28,100 --> 00:47:30,100
Go, go, go.

468
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:49,600
As your family's oldest friend, I'm
always chosen to bring you messages.

469
00:47:52,100 --> 00:47:55,100
Tell me, Don Altobello.

470
00:47:56,800 --> 00:48:00,800
Your old partners are grateful
for the money you made them.

471
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:03,500
They worship you...

472
00:48:04,600 --> 00:48:10,400
...but their hearts are broken
because they think you abandoned them.

473
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:17,100
They want to share your deal
on lmmobiliare, to be a family again.

474
00:48:17,700 --> 00:48:20,300
It can purify their money.

475
00:48:22,400 --> 00:48:24,900
This I cannot do.

476
00:48:26,900 --> 00:48:30,700
Immobiliare must be legitimate.

477
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:34,400
I know.

478
00:48:34,700 --> 00:48:37,200
But they're unhappy.

479
00:48:38,900 --> 00:48:40,700
And you?

480
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:46,900
I ask nothing for myself,
only peace in my old age.

481
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:50,800
But I must please the world around me.

482
00:48:52,100 --> 00:48:58,300
Michael, your father was
a reasonable man. Learn from him.

483
00:49:00,700 --> 00:49:04,200
I learned many things from my father.

484
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:15,100
Call a meeting, my friend,
so there are no debts or grudges.

485
00:49:16,500 --> 00:49:19,600
We will make the peace, you and I.

486
00:49:27,700 --> 00:49:29,600
(ITALIAN RADIO) The Vatican
announced today

487
00:49:29,900 --> 00:49:34,000
that Pope Paul VI has cancelled
his Sunday blessing

488
00:49:34,400 --> 00:49:36,500
due to ill health.

489
00:49:36,800 --> 00:49:42,300
His physician has ordered total bedrest

490
00:49:42,600 --> 00:49:45,400
and cessation of all activities.

491
00:49:45,700 --> 00:49:47,700
(RADIO CONTINUES)

492
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:04,600
They've had a press conference. The
Pope's condition is grave. "Gravissimo."

493
00:50:20,800 --> 00:50:23,000
(THEY PRAY)

494
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:35,900
Gentlemen, the purpose
of this meeting is to establish

495
00:50:36,300 --> 00:50:41,100
that we all agree to what was decided
at the shareholder meeting in New York.

496
00:50:42,000 --> 00:50:44,000
Please...

497
00:50:44,300 --> 00:50:48,800
Our group represents a consortium
of Catholic businessmen

498
00:50:49,100 --> 00:50:52,100
against the Corleone control.

499
00:50:52,800 --> 00:50:57,600
The Vatican has cast its vote. Corleone
Group already controls the Board.

500
00:50:58,100 --> 00:51:02,600
According to the Lateran Treaty,
the Vatican vote must be ratified here.

501
00:51:03,000 --> 00:51:05,500
Here in Rome, by the Pope.

502
00:51:09,100 --> 00:51:12,500
The Pope is gravely ill.

503
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:17,700
Until he recovers, I am powerless.

504
00:51:18,400 --> 00:51:21,300
- What if he dies?
- Then...

505
00:51:22,400 --> 00:51:25,500
...as you Americans say,
all bets are off.

506
00:51:25,800 --> 00:51:28,400
Gentlemen, please.

507
00:51:29,300 --> 00:51:33,400
This is a brief delay. Nothing more.

508
00:51:37,500 --> 00:51:40,800
Your Excellency, gentlemen...

509
00:51:41,400 --> 00:51:46,900
I advise you to join us in our prayers
for the Holy Father's recovery.

510
00:51:48,100 --> 00:51:49,800
We had an agreement!

511
00:51:51,200 --> 00:51:54,900
This meeting was to be
merely a formality.

512
00:51:55,200 --> 00:52:00,100
- Please sit down.
- I'd rather stand. Give me an answer.

513
00:52:00,500 --> 00:52:05,800
The lmmobiliare has its roots in the
European tradition. Please understand.

514
00:52:06,700 --> 00:52:10,000
I understand.
Your tactics are despicable.

515
00:52:10,300 --> 00:52:13,300
That's quite an indictment,
coming from a Corleone.

516
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:18,600
- Gentlemen, gentlemen!
- Remember you are in the Vatican.

517
00:52:21,500 --> 00:52:27,400
- What is it that you want?
- Yes, you will take control.

518
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:32,200
We'll gladly put you at the helm
of our little fleet,

519
00:52:32,500 --> 00:52:36,400
but our ships must all sail
in the same direction.

520
00:52:38,000 --> 00:52:43,900
Otherwise, who can say how long
your stay with us will last?

521
00:52:45,800 --> 00:52:52,100
It's not personal. It's only business.
You should know, Godfather.

522
00:52:55,700 --> 00:52:57,100
Very well.

523
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:03,200
You want to do business with me?
I will do business with you.

524
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:07,000
Vipers, all of them.

525
00:53:12,400 --> 00:53:15,400
- We're back with the Borgias!
- Uncle Michael...

526
00:53:15,700 --> 00:53:18,500
- Andrew!
- I heard you were here.

527
00:53:18,800 --> 00:53:23,000
It's so nice to see you.
Vincent, it's so nice.

528
00:53:23,400 --> 00:53:26,400
What is this about the Borgias?
Those days are over.

529
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:35,000
- Recognise it?
- Yeah.

530
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:40,500
Genco Olive Oil. That's where our
grandfather started as a delivery boy.

531
00:53:40,900 --> 00:53:43,700
Three years later he owned it.

532
00:53:44,300 --> 00:53:47,300
- Only in America.
- That's it.

533
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:52,600
Vincenzo, where have you been hiding?
We need your help so badly.

534
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:57,000
- What can I do for you?
- Get rid of Joe Zasa. He sells drugs...

535
00:53:57,300 --> 00:54:01,600
Now that I'm an older woman,
I'm afraid to go out at night.

536
00:54:02,000 --> 00:54:04,200
Where should they be now?

537
00:54:04,400 --> 00:54:07,400
- Lou, what's going on?
- We're late.

538
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:11,900
- Have I ever let you down?
- I trust you.

539
00:54:12,100 --> 00:54:14,400
- Don't worry.
- Thank you.

540
00:54:14,700 --> 00:54:16,400
Enjoy yourselves.

541
00:54:23,000 --> 00:54:27,300
- What was that?
- The neighbourhood's in trouble.

542
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:30,500
- Do you keep an eye out for them?
- Yes.

543
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:33,700
- And for me?
- From now on.

544
00:54:34,600 --> 00:54:38,400
- I've missed you all this time.
- I missed you too, cousin.

545
00:54:38,800 --> 00:54:43,800
I missed growing up with my cousins.
I didn't even know you, but missed you.

546
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:48,900
Do you remember stories
about our fathers? The old days?

547
00:54:49,300 --> 00:54:52,300
Yeah, what do you want to know?

548
00:54:54,000 --> 00:54:59,700
- What was Sonny like?
- Well, he was the Prince of the City.

549
00:55:00,900 --> 00:55:04,700
He died before I was born,
but I've heard a lot about him.

550
00:55:06,400 --> 00:55:10,000
- What about my father?
- He's a great man.

551
00:55:11,400 --> 00:55:14,100
He's a hero. He saved the family.

552
00:55:15,500 --> 00:55:17,500
- Vincent?
- What?

553
00:55:17,800 --> 00:55:20,300
Did he kill his own brother?

554
00:55:24,500 --> 00:55:26,300
No.

555
00:55:28,300 --> 00:55:30,700
So, it's all lies?

556
00:55:34,100 --> 00:55:37,700
Just stories, sweetheart. OK?

557
00:55:41,600 --> 00:55:43,300
OK.

558
00:55:44,700 --> 00:55:46,900
I believe you.

559
00:55:47,200 --> 00:55:51,100
- I'm glad you're around.
- I'm glad you're here too.

560
00:55:55,700 --> 00:55:57,700
Cugina...

561
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:00,000
Cuz...

562
00:56:13,900 --> 00:56:17,200
I'd like to take Joey Zasa
for a ride and drop him.

563
00:56:17,400 --> 00:56:20,100
Joey Zasa is nothing.

564
00:56:20,300 --> 00:56:24,000
He's a small-time enforcer.
He bluffs and threatens.

565
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:28,200
He's nothing. You can see him coming
a mile away.

566
00:56:29,100 --> 00:56:32,100
- We should kill him before he...
- No!

567
00:56:34,700 --> 00:56:39,300
Never hate your enemies.
It affects your judgement.

568
00:56:55,300 --> 00:56:57,900
Nice to see you again, Mr Corleone.

569
00:57:18,400 --> 00:57:21,000
Hey, girls. Let's go.

570
00:57:38,300 --> 00:57:42,600
We trusted you to manage
our money in the casinos.

571
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:48,600
It's not even 20 years. You've sold the
casinos and made fortunes for all of us.

572
00:57:49,000 --> 00:57:51,300
Bravo, Don Corleone!

573
00:57:53,200 --> 00:57:54,500
Thank you.

574
00:57:55,500 --> 00:58:02,500
Friends, I have come here
because our business together is done.

575
00:58:04,000 --> 00:58:05,700
We have prospered,

576
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:11,700
and now it is time for us to dissolve
the business relationship between us.

577
00:58:13,200 --> 00:58:15,200
That's it.

578
00:58:15,300 --> 00:58:18,700
But I do have a little surprise. Al?

579
00:58:21,300 --> 00:58:23,800
Your shares in the casinos.

580
00:58:24,100 --> 00:58:28,100
I've cut the red tape, so you could
get your money right away.

581
00:58:34,800 --> 00:58:37,100
50 million dollars!

582
00:58:37,300 --> 00:58:40,600
- Not everybody gets the same.
- Nothing for you...

583
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:46,600
- It depends on your investment.
- Michael, this is really generous!

584
00:58:47,000 --> 00:58:48,300
Wonderful!

585
00:58:48,600 --> 00:58:51,100
(WHISTLES) Grazie!

586
00:58:51,400 --> 00:58:56,500
- Parisi, how much did you invest?
- I don't remember.

587
00:58:56,900 --> 00:58:58,800
You're blessed.

588
00:59:03,500 --> 00:59:08,700
My family has done much of
the hard work, taken many risks.

589
00:59:10,600 --> 00:59:13,500
All to make money
for the rest of the families.

590
00:59:16,000 --> 00:59:18,500
You all know Joey Zasa.

591
00:59:18,900 --> 00:59:21,900
He is, I admit, an important man.

592
00:59:22,600 --> 00:59:26,700
His picture is on the cover
of the New York Times magazine.

593
00:59:27,100 --> 00:59:31,700
He gets the Esquire Magazine award
for the best-dressed gangster.

594
00:59:32,100 --> 00:59:33,900
The newspapers praise him

595
00:59:34,200 --> 00:59:38,600
because he hires Blacks,
which shows he has a good heart.

596
00:59:41,300 --> 00:59:43,500
He is famous.

597
00:59:43,800 --> 00:59:49,600
Who knows? Maybe one day
he'll make all of you popular.

598
00:59:51,500 --> 00:59:52,800
It's true.

599
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:58,200
I make more of a bella figura.
That is my nature.

600
00:59:58,700 --> 01:00:03,400
But I also want to make a move
into legitimate enterprises.

601
01:00:03,800 --> 01:00:06,400
I'd like a little pin from the Pope.

602
01:00:06,900 --> 01:00:11,800
Sure, I take the Blacks and the Spanish
into my family,

603
01:00:12,100 --> 01:00:15,300
because that's America.

604
01:00:16,200 --> 01:00:20,200
And you guarantee
that they don't deal drugs?

605
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:26,500
I don't guarantee that. I guarantee
that I'll kill anybody who does.

606
01:00:30,500 --> 01:00:35,600
- Let me talk to him.
- Who can refuse Don Altobello?

607
01:00:36,100 --> 01:00:39,000
- Joey, are you...
- No!

608
01:00:39,200 --> 01:00:44,800
I say to all of you: I have been
treated this day with no respect.

609
01:00:45,900 --> 01:00:50,900
I've earned you all money.
I've made you rich and I asked for little.

610
01:00:51,300 --> 01:00:55,600
Good. You will not give, so I'll take!

611
01:00:56,700 --> 01:00:59,100
As for Don Corleone,

612
01:00:59,500 --> 01:01:05,300
he makes it very clear to me today
that he is my enemy.

613
01:01:09,100 --> 01:01:11,800
You must choose between us.

614
01:01:16,000 --> 01:01:17,600
No, Joey!

615
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:21,600
Michael, we could reason together.

616
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:23,500
No.

617
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:29,000
Michael, please... let's agree.

618
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:31,600
He doesn't know what he's...

619
01:01:31,900 --> 01:01:33,700
No, no.

620
01:01:37,800 --> 01:01:41,200
Michael, the news is everywhere.

621
01:01:42,200 --> 01:01:45,700
Everyone says that you
control lmmobiliare.

622
01:01:46,100 --> 01:01:51,400
Immobiliare is already laundering
money in Peru and Nassau.

623
01:01:52,500 --> 01:01:57,000
We've worked with you for 40 years.
We should wet our beaks a little.

624
01:01:57,400 --> 01:02:02,400
- We want to do business with you.
- That's right, we've been together...

625
01:02:11,800 --> 01:02:15,100
- It's a hit! Let's go!
- Let's get out of here! Move!

626
01:02:34,300 --> 01:02:37,100
My coat! It's my lucky coat!

627
01:02:38,300 --> 01:02:40,300
It's my lucky coat!

628
01:02:46,300 --> 01:02:48,700
Stay behind me!

629
01:03:03,900 --> 01:03:05,700
Mikey, this way!

630
01:03:14,400 --> 01:03:17,400
Zasa, you son-of-a-bitch...

631
01:03:38,100 --> 01:03:40,600
Come on. We're out of here.

632
01:04:12,500 --> 01:04:15,000
- You did good, Vincent.
- Grazie.

633
01:04:15,300 --> 01:04:18,700
The old Dons were pretty much
wiped out.

634
01:04:18,900 --> 01:04:21,800
The survivors made deals with Zasa.

635
01:04:23,100 --> 01:04:25,500
- Altobello?
- He survived.

636
01:04:25,700 --> 01:04:30,800
He's with his daughters in Staten Island.
He says he's going to retire in Sicily.

637
01:04:32,500 --> 01:04:37,400
Joey Zasa would never pull something
like this without the backing.

638
01:04:37,700 --> 01:04:43,200
He's just muscle. He doesn't have
the wit for that helicopter attack.

639
01:04:43,600 --> 01:04:47,800
He doesn't even have the ambition
to wipe out the whole Commission.

640
01:04:48,100 --> 01:04:50,900
I say we hit back and take Zasa out!

641
01:04:56,300 --> 01:04:59,300
Never let anyone know
what you're thinking.

642
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:10,400
Let's get a message to Joey Zasa.

643
01:05:13,600 --> 01:05:16,400
I respect what he's done.

644
01:05:17,100 --> 01:05:20,200
The new overthrows the old. It's natural.

645
01:05:20,400 --> 01:05:24,100
How can you do business
with this guy?

646
01:05:25,400 --> 01:05:29,400
I'm a businessman, first and foremost.
I want no further conflict.

647
01:05:29,700 --> 01:05:34,500
- Tell him that he can live or he can die.
- Vincent, will you shut up!

648
01:05:52,600 --> 01:05:54,600
That's it.

649
01:05:56,400 --> 01:05:58,300
Joey Zasa...

650
01:05:58,500 --> 01:06:01,200
He can't be doing this alone.

651
01:06:04,500 --> 01:06:09,300
Just when I thought I was out,
they pull me back in.

652
01:06:17,200 --> 01:06:22,800
Our true enemy has not yet
shown his face.

653
01:06:27,500 --> 01:06:29,200
Michael!

654
01:06:35,700 --> 01:06:39,700
- Has he had his medicine?
- I don't know what he took.

655
01:06:42,200 --> 01:06:46,000
- I've got my wind back.
- Call a doctor.

656
01:06:46,300 --> 01:06:49,000
- Run, run, run!
- Vincent!

657
01:06:49,300 --> 01:06:51,400
Run at thunder, girl! Thunder can't hurt!

658
01:06:53,200 --> 01:06:55,700
Harmless noise!

659
01:06:55,900 --> 01:07:00,500
Bullshit! You deceitful old fuck!

660
01:07:01,400 --> 01:07:03,800
Altobello, you fuck!

661
01:07:07,000 --> 01:07:08,800
Fredo!

662
01:07:09,300 --> 01:07:10,700
Fredo!

663
01:07:34,300 --> 01:07:37,200
Oh, God! Dad!

664
01:07:39,300 --> 01:07:41,400
Excuse me.

665
01:07:41,700 --> 01:07:43,700
I'll call Kay.

666
01:07:54,000 --> 01:07:58,000
- Good evening, sir.
- Can we wait here? We'll be back soon.

667
01:08:04,400 --> 01:08:10,700
Mr Harrison, you said it was urgent.
Have you come to confess your sins?

668
01:08:11,200 --> 01:08:16,100
Michael Corleone has had a diabetic
stroke. I wanted you to know about it.

669
01:08:16,500 --> 01:08:21,100
He's in a coma. I'm here to insist
the deal goes through in any event.

670
01:08:21,500 --> 01:08:23,500
The Pope has not much time left.

671
01:08:25,200 --> 01:08:29,100
So, as you, I am in a difficult position.

672
01:08:29,300 --> 01:08:33,200
We have to ratify this deal
as soon as possible.

673
01:08:33,500 --> 01:08:36,500
- We have an understanding.
- Good.

674
01:08:37,600 --> 01:08:41,600
- I'm going to the hospital.
- I'll pray for Mr Corleone.

675
01:08:45,900 --> 01:08:49,900
- Our thoughts are with Mr Corleone.
- Thank you, Father Jim.

676
01:08:52,500 --> 01:08:56,800
Everything would be out in the open
if Corleone dies.

677
01:08:57,600 --> 01:08:59,700
Play for time, Keinszig.

678
01:09:00,500 --> 01:09:05,200
A habit born of a long contemplation
of eternity.

679
01:09:11,700 --> 01:09:15,700
- Forget about it, Vinnie.
- Why? It's a simple hit.

680
01:09:16,000 --> 01:09:21,700
I'd love to smack Joey Zasa and then
whack the fag. But it's impossible.

681
01:09:22,100 --> 01:09:27,400
He's always with people, in front of TV
cameras in his own neighbourhood.

682
01:09:27,700 --> 01:09:31,100
- It's not impossible. It'll work for us.
- How?

683
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:36,200
Do you think he's going to let
Uncle Michael survive? Would you?

684
01:09:36,500 --> 01:09:39,300
He may not survive anyway.

685
01:09:39,900 --> 01:09:43,600
- How would you do it?
- I'd do it myself.

686
01:09:45,300 --> 01:09:47,300
Do it!

687
01:09:49,100 --> 01:09:52,000
- What would you need?
- A couple of guys.

688
01:10:22,900 --> 01:10:25,200
Hello, Michael.

689
01:10:27,600 --> 01:10:29,600
It's Kay.

690
01:10:34,100 --> 01:10:35,700
Kay...

691
01:10:37,900 --> 01:10:40,300
I never expected you.

692
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:43,000
No, I know.

693
01:10:45,400 --> 01:10:47,200
But I'm here.

694
01:10:51,000 --> 01:10:53,400
- I'm glad.
- You know...

695
01:10:56,400 --> 01:10:59,000
I've never seen you looking so helpless.

696
01:11:03,600 --> 01:11:06,100
It's not so bad, really.

697
01:11:07,600 --> 01:11:11,900
I feel... l'm getting wiser now.

698
01:11:12,300 --> 01:11:14,600
- Yeah.
- Oh, yeah.

699
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:21,000
- The sicker you get, the wiser you get?
- When I'm dead, I'll be really smart.

700
01:11:22,600 --> 01:11:27,000
Michael... I want to thank you for Tony.

701
01:11:30,000 --> 01:11:34,200
He's doing really well.
He's gotten some very good notices,

702
01:11:34,500 --> 01:11:40,000
and he'll make his operatic debut
in Sicily, in Palermo this Easter, so...

703
01:11:41,700 --> 01:11:43,300
So, thank you.

704
01:11:44,500 --> 01:11:48,000
That's a real honour. In Sicily.

705
01:11:52,800 --> 01:11:55,900
I will be there. I won't miss that.

706
01:11:56,700 --> 01:11:58,500
I won't miss that.

707
01:12:04,600 --> 01:12:07,000
Mary, Tony...

708
01:12:08,400 --> 01:12:10,600
Go see Dad.

709
01:12:15,800 --> 01:12:19,300
- Sweetheart!
- Everything's going to be all right.

710
01:12:19,800 --> 01:12:22,800
- Tony!
- How are you doing, Pop?

711
01:12:25,100 --> 01:12:28,300
Your mother told me what happened.

712
01:12:28,600 --> 01:12:34,200
- About Palermo? I hope you'll be there.
- Of course. Kiss me.

713
01:12:53,900 --> 01:12:59,400
- Cousin Vinnie?
- He's not here. Call his apartmen

714
01:12:59,900 --> 01:13:03,300
- It's your cousin Mary.
- Let her in.

715
01:13:07,400 --> 01:13:11,300
Hi, cuz. I thought I'd drop by.
Is that OK?

716
01:13:11,700 --> 01:13:14,200
I'll get the guys.

717
01:13:15,400 --> 01:13:18,900
No, it's not OK.
You shouldn't have come, Mary.

718
01:13:20,100 --> 01:13:22,400
Only a couple of minutes, OK?

719
01:13:23,900 --> 01:13:27,200
- You look beautiful, cuz.
- Thanks.

720
01:13:29,700 --> 01:13:33,000
So this is your club, your hideout?

721
01:13:33,400 --> 01:13:36,500
- Yeah.
- I came here to check it out.

722
01:13:40,900 --> 01:13:44,900
It's so strange, just me
and Aunt Connie in the house.

723
01:13:45,100 --> 01:13:49,600
- I feel better when I'm with you.
- What's wrong, sweetheart?

724
01:13:50,000 --> 01:13:52,600
- I'm scared about my father.
- Don't be.

725
01:13:52,800 --> 01:13:57,200
When they took him out of
the ambulance, I thought he was dead.

726
01:13:57,500 --> 01:14:00,500
Everybody says he's going to be better.

727
01:14:01,500 --> 01:14:03,500
Don't worry.

728
01:14:03,800 --> 01:14:06,500
I remember a shooting when I was little.

729
01:14:07,900 --> 01:14:12,700
And one time Al Neri and other
bodyguards took me and Tony away.

730
01:14:14,300 --> 01:14:17,300
Is it all happening again?

731
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:20,500
Not like that, sweetie.

732
01:14:21,800 --> 01:14:26,200
Then why are you hiding here?
Is something going to happen to you?

733
01:14:27,400 --> 01:14:32,100
Nothing's going to happen to me,
cugina. We'll take care of you.

734
01:14:42,700 --> 01:14:47,100
- Can I stay here and hide out with you?
- Can you help me cook for the boys?

735
01:14:47,400 --> 01:14:51,400
You know that I don't know
how to cook, but I'll help.

736
01:15:04,000 --> 01:15:06,000
OK...

737
01:15:06,200 --> 01:15:08,200
What do I do?

738
01:15:40,100 --> 01:15:43,500
- I love you, cuz.
- I love you, too.

739
01:15:46,900 --> 01:15:49,300
Let us cook.

740
01:16:05,400 --> 01:16:07,400
Hold me.

741
01:16:43,600 --> 01:16:48,100
You in the press and the police
use words like "Mafia", "Cosa Nostra".

742
01:16:48,400 --> 01:16:53,700
This is a fantasy. We Italian-Americans
laid the bricks that built this city.

743
01:16:54,100 --> 01:16:56,600
We have Meucci,
who invented the telephone.

744
01:16:56,900 --> 01:17:00,400
We have Don Ameche,
who played the guy who invented it.

745
01:17:00,700 --> 01:17:04,600
Buy yourself a raffle ticket,
maybe you'll win a Cadillac.

746
01:17:06,000 --> 01:17:08,400
The salsiccia is wonderful!

747
01:17:08,800 --> 01:17:10,900
Here, have a sandwich.

748
01:17:23,700 --> 01:17:27,600
- Nice to see you, Mr Zasa.
- Have a nice time.

749
01:17:28,700 --> 01:17:31,700
Don't forget to buy your raffle tickets.

750
01:17:34,200 --> 01:17:37,400
- What are you doing?
- He didn't mean it.

751
01:17:37,700 --> 01:17:41,000
- Tell him you're sorry.
- OK, let's go.

752
01:17:59,400 --> 01:18:01,900
Joey! How are you?

753
01:18:02,900 --> 01:18:05,500
How are you, buddy boy?

754
01:18:05,800 --> 01:18:09,400
Hey, Joey Zasa! Joey, up your ass!

755
01:18:10,800 --> 01:18:13,500
- Who is this? Do you know him?
- Ignore him.

756
01:18:13,800 --> 01:18:17,400
Who's going to win the car? The Ant?

757
01:18:19,100 --> 01:18:23,300
This is what gives Italian-Americans
a bad name. A cappone like this.

758
01:18:23,700 --> 01:18:25,900
Joey, up your ass!

759
01:18:26,200 --> 01:18:29,000
Get off the car!
Do you have a raffle ticket?

760
01:18:30,000 --> 01:18:33,200
Joey, take a look at my raffle ticket!

761
01:18:34,200 --> 01:18:37,600
Here's what I think of you...
and your raffle ticket.

762
01:18:37,900 --> 01:18:41,500
Get the fuck off this car.
I'll break your fucking balls.

763
01:18:44,100 --> 01:18:46,700
Get out of here!

764
01:19:02,300 --> 01:19:05,600
Run, Joey! You piece of shit!

765
01:19:17,600 --> 01:19:18,900
Open the door!

766
01:19:19,600 --> 01:19:22,300
How are you, Joe?

767
01:19:24,600 --> 01:19:26,000
Zasa!

768
01:19:43,600 --> 01:19:50,200
Don't ever again give that kind of order.
Not while I'm alive.

769
01:19:50,900 --> 01:19:52,700
Understand?

770
01:19:53,900 --> 01:19:59,900
You were too sick to make a decision.
I got a go-ahead from Neri and Connie.

771
01:20:00,900 --> 01:20:02,700
Connie?

772
01:20:12,100 --> 01:20:15,200
It was the right decision, Uncle Mike.

773
01:20:15,500 --> 01:20:19,200
It was the wrong decision.
I command this family!

774
01:20:19,900 --> 01:20:22,000
Right or wrong...

775
01:20:22,800 --> 01:20:25,700
...it was not what I wanted!

776
01:20:44,200 --> 01:20:46,100
Do you understand?

777
01:20:52,700 --> 01:20:54,000
Yes.

778
01:21:00,700 --> 01:21:02,400
Come on, Michael.

779
01:21:14,200 --> 01:21:16,000
Yes.

780
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:23,300
Good. Vincent, help me to my bed.
I want to talk to you alone for a minute.

781
01:21:31,700 --> 01:21:36,300
You know, I always felt
responsible for you.

782
01:21:36,600 --> 01:21:38,700
You know that.

783
01:21:39,100 --> 01:21:40,900
Your father...

784
01:21:41,900 --> 01:21:45,200
...my brother, we were opposites.

785
01:21:45,500 --> 01:21:50,400
We would fight and argue.
But I never doubted his love.

786
01:21:50,800 --> 01:21:55,400
He would do anything for me.
But his temper...

787
01:21:58,900 --> 01:22:03,000
Too much. It clouded his reason.

788
01:22:04,300 --> 01:22:07,500
I don't want you to make that mistake.

789
01:22:09,700 --> 01:22:12,000
Also...

790
01:22:12,300 --> 01:22:15,300
...he, too, had a way with women.

791
01:22:16,600 --> 01:22:19,100
- Vincent...
- So I hear.

792
01:22:19,400 --> 01:22:21,800
What are you doing with my daughter?

793
01:22:24,600 --> 01:22:27,600
What are you doing with her?

794
01:22:31,300 --> 01:22:33,500
It's too dangerous.

795
01:22:36,200 --> 01:22:38,200
Do you hear me?

796
01:22:43,900 --> 01:22:45,900
OK.

797
01:22:59,800 --> 01:23:01,900
Vincenzo...

798
01:23:05,400 --> 01:23:10,200
When they come,
they'll come at what you love.

799
01:23:17,800 --> 01:23:21,000
Michael, you must lead another life.

800
01:23:21,300 --> 01:23:26,600
You have everything a man could
desire. It's time for you to retire.

801
01:23:27,500 --> 01:23:30,300
I have too much responsibility.

802
01:23:31,200 --> 01:23:36,600
Immobiliare? It's too difficult now.
You should really get out.

803
01:23:37,100 --> 01:23:41,900
What do you know
about those pezzi da novanta in Italy?

804
01:23:45,600 --> 01:23:49,300
I'm too old to know anything
about those new people.

805
01:23:49,600 --> 01:23:54,200
I must accept my age
and grow my olives and tomatoes.

806
01:23:55,500 --> 01:23:59,700
- We're not that old.
- But you're very ill.

807
01:24:00,400 --> 01:24:05,000
Michael... Let me see
what can be done.

808
01:24:05,400 --> 01:24:09,600
Let me work to make your path
a little easier.

809
01:24:09,900 --> 01:24:15,300
- Your friendship does that always.
- That makes me happy.

810
01:24:15,700 --> 01:24:19,700
Joey Zasa...
You were wrong about him.

811
01:24:20,800 --> 01:24:24,600
I trust too much.
That's always been my fault.

812
01:24:32,300 --> 01:24:36,200
Michael... treachery is everywhere.

813
01:24:36,400 --> 01:24:40,700
You still have your fingers
on the strings, even now.

814
01:24:41,900 --> 01:24:44,900
Let's see more of each other.

815
01:24:45,100 --> 01:24:49,500
- Michael, in Sicily?
- In Sicily.

816
01:24:50,300 --> 01:24:52,300
In Sicilia.

817
01:24:52,600 --> 01:24:55,100
In Sicilia.

818
01:25:42,400 --> 01:25:44,400
How are you?

819
01:25:44,600 --> 01:25:47,100
Don Bendino, my old friend.

820
01:26:18,900 --> 01:26:24,300
I brought you here so that my old friend
and protector, Don Tommasino,

821
01:26:24,700 --> 01:26:26,700
could advise us.

822
01:26:27,000 --> 01:26:30,900
Don Tommasino,
what do you think of Altobello?

823
01:26:33,100 --> 01:26:35,100
A very talented man.

824
01:26:35,300 --> 01:26:39,900
He's kept the peace between
our Sicilian and American friends.

825
01:26:40,200 --> 01:26:42,800
The saint of reason.

826
01:26:44,700 --> 01:26:48,600
A blood-bath in Atlantic City
left New York a mess.

827
01:26:48,900 --> 01:26:51,900
Joey Zasa at least was running
a tight ship,

828
01:26:52,200 --> 01:26:55,900
but with him out of the picture
we must step in.

829
01:26:56,300 --> 01:27:00,600
- Step back in.
- Or the Chinese and Colombians will.

830
01:27:00,900 --> 01:27:06,200
The Corleones didn't do drugs, so New
York is weak and Palermo is strong.

831
01:27:07,400 --> 01:27:11,400
Your enemies always get strong
on what you leave behind.

832
01:27:12,200 --> 01:27:18,300
Don Tommasino, who could give
the order for that massacre...

833
01:27:20,900 --> 01:27:24,600
...and still pressure the Vatican deal?

834
01:27:24,900 --> 01:27:29,600
Only Lucchesi, a man in two worlds.

835
01:27:31,800 --> 01:27:35,700
"Our ships must all sail
in the same direction"...

836
01:27:37,000 --> 01:27:42,500
Italian politics have had these men
for centuries. They are the true Mafia.

837
01:27:43,000 --> 01:27:46,100
The Archbishop and the Vatican Bank,
that's the big problem.

838
01:27:46,400 --> 01:27:50,500
They're the same problem, B.J.
They're connected.

839
01:27:51,200 --> 01:27:53,700
The Archbishop has powerful friends.

840
01:27:56,500 --> 01:27:58,400
They totally protect him.

841
01:27:58,700 --> 01:28:02,900
Is there someone in the Church
who can assist us?

842
01:28:03,300 --> 01:28:06,900
Someone who is honourable?

843
01:28:08,100 --> 01:28:10,100
Cardinal Lamberto.

844
01:28:10,400 --> 01:28:15,600
A good and wise man. Very influential.

845
01:28:15,900 --> 01:28:18,800
He will receive you.

846
01:28:23,900 --> 01:28:29,600
I will see this Cardinal Lamberto
and see if we can work things out.

847
01:28:31,500 --> 01:28:36,200
You honour your agreements,
but you are dealing with crooks.

848
01:28:36,900 --> 01:28:39,400
They have no honour.

849
01:28:41,200 --> 01:28:42,900
My word is final.

850
01:28:53,600 --> 01:28:57,400
Politics and crime,
they're the same thing.

851
01:29:13,700 --> 01:29:16,500
Bravo! Bravo!

852
01:29:20,100 --> 01:29:26,500
I've invited you all here to celebrate
my son's dbut in an opera house...

853
01:29:27,000 --> 01:29:30,000
We'll play "Philadelphia".

854
01:29:30,300 --> 01:29:34,500
Seven cards. Two down, four up.
Deuces and one-eyed jacks are wild.

855
01:29:34,900 --> 01:29:37,400
...in the opera "Cavallaria Rusticana".

856
01:29:37,800 --> 01:29:41,400
- It's "Cavalleria Rusticana", Dad.
- "Cavalleria".

857
01:29:41,600 --> 01:29:46,600
I think I have tickets to the wrong opera.
I've been in New York too long.

858
01:29:47,800 --> 01:29:51,100
You will all receive tickets,
so come on time.

859
01:29:51,400 --> 01:29:54,400
Dad, I've got a present for you.

860
01:29:57,200 --> 01:30:01,700
It comes from the town of Corleone
and it's authentic Sicilian.

861
01:30:03,000 --> 01:30:06,300
And... I learned it for you.

862
01:30:15,500 --> 01:30:18,100
(SINGS SICILIAN LOVE SONG)

863
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:41,100
She was wonderful, beautiful.
I loved her. And then she died.

864
01:31:42,400 --> 01:31:47,400
My trusted bodyguard
planted a bomb in my car.

865
01:31:49,100 --> 01:31:52,000
She drove it before I did.

866
01:31:52,700 --> 01:31:56,200
Why is such a beautiful country
so violent?

867
01:31:56,500 --> 01:31:57,800
History.

868
01:31:58,100 --> 01:32:02,600
Mom was telling me about when your
biggest worry was passing your exams.

869
01:32:03,000 --> 01:32:06,400
- Yes, it was then.
- I worry about you now.

870
01:32:06,700 --> 01:32:11,700
Oh, Mary, you're such a
warm-hearted girl. You always were.

871
01:32:12,200 --> 01:32:15,900
- I love my family.
- Even your cousin Vincent?

872
01:32:19,700 --> 01:32:21,700
I really love him.

873
01:32:23,000 --> 01:32:27,100
- He's your first cousin.
- Then I love him first.

874
01:32:27,500 --> 01:32:30,200
Mary, you can't see him.

875
01:32:30,800 --> 01:32:33,600
Just don't see him any more.

876
01:32:33,900 --> 01:32:37,600
He's right. It's too dangerous.

877
01:32:39,700 --> 01:32:42,700
Mary, you can't see him any more.

878
01:32:43,000 --> 01:32:45,400
- Not in that fashion.
- No.

879
01:32:47,000 --> 01:32:50,500
- Please, promise me.
- No!

880
01:32:50,700 --> 01:32:52,800
- Obey me on this.
- No, Dad!

881
01:32:58,300 --> 01:33:02,800
Mary is smart, Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

882
01:33:18,100 --> 01:33:20,700
(MUSIC: "MIRACLE MAN"
BY ELVIS COSTELLO)

883
01:33:25,500 --> 01:33:28,500
Bella cugina... Tesoro mio.

884
01:33:39,700 --> 01:33:42,700
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

885
01:33:43,000 --> 01:33:46,500
I want you to do something for me.
It's dangerous.

886
01:33:48,400 --> 01:33:51,800
Good. I'm in. What do you need?

887
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:55,600
I want you to sell your soul
to Don Altobello.

888
01:33:56,000 --> 01:33:58,400
To betray me.

889
01:34:01,100 --> 01:34:03,900
He'd never believe me.

890
01:34:04,100 --> 01:34:07,300
- That depends.
- Sit down.

891
01:34:09,600 --> 01:34:12,000
I have an idea.

892
01:34:12,700 --> 01:34:17,100
See if you can learn
how high Altobello is connected.

893
01:34:20,300 --> 01:34:22,600
Arrange a meeting.

894
01:34:24,800 --> 01:34:29,700
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

895
01:34:30,300 --> 01:34:33,800
- Ask for his help.
- What problems?

896
01:34:35,300 --> 01:34:38,500
That you want to run away
with my daughter.

897
01:34:38,700 --> 01:34:43,500
But you know that if you do,
I will become your enemy.

898
01:34:47,700 --> 01:34:51,300
- You know that I would never do that.
- I know.

899
01:34:52,500 --> 01:34:57,400
Ask Altobello to speak to me.
To further the marriage.

900
01:34:57,800 --> 01:35:03,100
But you're cousins, after all. Michael
was always a little old-fashioned.

901
01:35:03,600 --> 01:35:08,600
Say you can't belong to my legitimate
world. That you want your own family.

902
01:35:09,400 --> 01:35:13,300
I could straighten out
what Joey Zasa left behind.

903
01:35:14,200 --> 01:35:17,400
I could use your friendship
to persuade him.

904
01:35:18,200 --> 01:35:21,300
I would be indebted to you forever.

905
01:35:23,100 --> 01:35:27,100
A Corleone knows the value
of such a friend.

906
01:35:28,500 --> 01:35:30,900
Then you would work for me?

907
01:35:32,000 --> 01:35:33,300
S.

908
01:35:36,000 --> 01:35:38,700
Bacio la mano, Don Altobello.

909
01:35:41,400 --> 01:35:46,300
If he hints that he wants you
to betray me, get insulted,

910
01:35:47,000 --> 01:35:49,700
because that's his trap.

911
01:35:56,300 --> 01:35:59,700
You're not telling me
the whole truth, Vincenzo.

912
01:36:02,700 --> 01:36:08,400
Isn't it true, that with Michael gone,
the girl controls everything?

913
01:36:12,200 --> 01:36:16,000
- Leave the girl out of this.
- Of course, you love her.

914
01:36:16,300 --> 01:36:18,700
And she loves you.

915
01:36:38,900 --> 01:36:41,500
I guessed it, didn't I?

916
01:36:43,300 --> 01:36:48,700
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.
I'll be learning a lot from you.

917
01:36:49,100 --> 01:36:53,100
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

918
01:36:54,900 --> 01:36:57,700
It's my duty to make the introductions.

919
01:37:04,900 --> 01:37:06,700
Don Lucchesi.

920
01:37:09,400 --> 01:37:14,900
Don Altobello tells me that you have
a strong character. A man of respect.

921
01:37:15,300 --> 01:37:18,700
This is the hero who put Joey Zasa
in his grave.

922
01:37:19,100 --> 01:37:23,300
If we'd known of his existence,
we wouldn't have backed Joey.

923
01:37:23,700 --> 01:37:26,100
No one wants another Joe.

924
01:37:27,500 --> 01:37:30,100
Let me be your friend.

925
01:37:30,500 --> 01:37:34,800
- Even the strongest man needs friends.
- I'm flattered.

926
01:37:36,000 --> 01:37:40,600
You're a man of finance and politics,
things I don't understand.

927
01:37:42,600 --> 01:37:46,700
You understand guns.
Finance is a gun.

928
01:37:47,400 --> 01:37:51,400
Politics is knowing
when to pull the trigger.

929
01:37:55,800 --> 01:37:58,100
How can I help?

930
01:37:58,400 --> 01:37:59,800
Vieni?

931
01:38:02,800 --> 01:38:08,200
Blessed is the peacemaker,
for he can be called the child of God.

932
01:38:08,600 --> 01:38:11,300
- Tu parli Italiano un poco?
- S.

933
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:36,800
The wheelchair for Don Tommasino.

934
01:38:44,800 --> 01:38:49,000
I trusted this business arrangement
with the Archbishop. I trusted him.

935
01:38:49,400 --> 01:38:53,100
I was sure his honesty
was beyond a doubt.

936
01:38:53,500 --> 01:38:58,300
But, as you see, I'm now
the victim of a swindle.

937
01:38:58,600 --> 01:39:04,400
He's stalling me. Vast monies have
gone to people in high political places

938
01:39:04,700 --> 01:39:07,400
and the Vatican Bank is the guarantor.

939
01:39:07,700 --> 01:39:12,900
If what you say is true,
there will be a great scandal.

940
01:39:15,100 --> 01:39:19,800
Look at this stone. It has been
in the water for a very long time,

941
01:39:20,100 --> 01:39:24,200
but the water has not penetrated it.

942
01:39:28,200 --> 01:39:29,600
Look...

943
01:39:30,700 --> 01:39:35,600
Perfectly dry. The same thing
has happened to men in Europe.

944
01:39:36,000 --> 01:39:40,400
For centuries they have been
surrounded by Christianity,

945
01:39:40,700 --> 01:39:46,500
but Christ has not penetrated.
Christ doesn't live within them.

946
01:39:50,600 --> 01:39:54,600
- What's happening?
- Could you get me something sweet?

947
01:39:54,900 --> 01:39:58,300
Some orange juice, candy...

948
01:40:02,100 --> 01:40:05,100
I have trouble with diabetes.

949
01:40:08,000 --> 01:40:10,500
My blood sugar goes low.

950
01:40:10,700 --> 01:40:12,800
I understand.

951
01:40:35,300 --> 01:40:38,700
It happens sometimes
when I'm under stress.

952
01:40:39,400 --> 01:40:41,700
I understand.

953
01:40:42,800 --> 01:40:47,000
To come to you
on such a delicate matter...

954
01:40:49,800 --> 01:40:54,700
Accusations against your Archbishop.
It was difficult for me.

955
01:40:56,100 --> 01:40:58,000
The mind suffers

956
01:40:58,100 --> 01:41:01,200
and the body cries out.

957
01:41:06,100 --> 01:41:08,100
That's true.

958
01:41:10,300 --> 01:41:14,300
Would you like to make
your confession?

959
01:41:21,000 --> 01:41:24,400
Your Eminence, I'm...

960
01:41:27,000 --> 01:41:32,900
It's been so long. I wouldn't...
I wouldn't know where to...

961
01:41:34,100 --> 01:41:36,100
It's been 30 years.

962
01:41:37,200 --> 01:41:40,600
I'd use up too much of your time, I think.

963
01:41:41,500 --> 01:41:43,900
I always have time to save souls.

964
01:41:45,300 --> 01:41:50,200
- Well, I'm beyond redemption.
- No, no...

965
01:41:59,600 --> 01:42:03,900
I hear the confessions
of my own priests here.

966
01:42:04,700 --> 01:42:08,400
Sometimes the desire to confess
is overwhelming,

967
01:42:08,700 --> 01:42:11,500
and we must seize the moment.

968
01:42:15,800 --> 01:42:20,400
What is the point of confessing
if I don't repent?

969
01:42:22,100 --> 01:42:25,500
I hear you are a practical man.

970
01:42:25,700 --> 01:42:28,200
What have you got to lose?

971
01:42:39,500 --> 01:42:41,600
Go on.

972
01:42:47,600 --> 01:42:49,900
I...

973
01:42:50,100 --> 01:42:52,400
...betrayed my wife.

974
01:42:53,700 --> 01:42:56,300
Go on, my son.

975
01:43:00,900 --> 01:43:03,400
I betrayed myself.

976
01:43:05,900 --> 01:43:08,100
I killed men.

977
01:43:11,400 --> 01:43:14,400
And I ordered men to be killed.

978
01:43:15,400 --> 01:43:18,000
Go on, my son. Go on.

979
01:43:23,400 --> 01:43:24,900
It's useless.

980
01:43:26,800 --> 01:43:28,800
Go on, my son.

981
01:43:29,800 --> 01:43:32,100
I killed...

982
01:43:36,400 --> 01:43:39,400
I ordered the death of my brother.

983
01:43:40,100 --> 01:43:42,200
He injured me.

984
01:43:43,500 --> 01:43:46,200
I killed my mother's son.

985
01:43:47,400 --> 01:43:49,800
I killed my father's son.

986
01:44:00,100 --> 01:44:04,900
Your sins are terrible,
and it is just that you suffer.

987
01:44:06,400 --> 01:44:09,600
Your life could be redeemed,

988
01:44:09,900 --> 01:44:14,500
but I know that you don't believe that.
You will not change.

989
01:44:18,100 --> 01:44:20,200
Ego te absolvo,

990
01:44:20,500 --> 01:44:23,700
in nomine Patris et Filiis
et Spiritu Sanctus. Amen.

991
01:44:37,700 --> 01:44:45,700
Pope Paul VI, Supreme Pontiff of the
Catholic Church, died last night at 9:40.

992
01:44:46,600 --> 01:44:50,500
He had been suffering from
bad health for several months.

993
01:44:50,900 --> 01:44:56,900
He was renowned for his intellectual and
spiritual qualities and his compassion.

994
01:44:57,200 --> 01:45:00,400
The loss is a cause
for profound mourning by all of us.

995
01:45:06,100 --> 01:45:08,100
Connie...

996
01:45:09,300 --> 01:45:14,000
All my life I've kept trying
to go up in society.

997
01:45:14,400 --> 01:45:18,800
To where everything higher up
was legal, straight...

998
01:45:19,500 --> 01:45:23,100
But the higher I go,
the more crooked it becomes.

999
01:45:25,600 --> 01:45:28,300
Where the hell does it end?

1000
01:45:36,700 --> 01:45:40,600
They've been killing each other
for centuries here.

1001
01:45:41,700 --> 01:45:45,900
For money, for pride, for family.

1002
01:45:48,900 --> 01:45:53,500
To keep from becoming the slaves
of the rich pezzi da novanta.

1003
01:46:00,100 --> 01:46:02,600
I made confession, Connie.

1004
01:46:03,400 --> 01:46:05,900
I confessed my sins.

1005
01:46:07,100 --> 01:46:12,600
Why? That's not like you. You don't
have to confess your sins to a stranger.

1006
01:46:12,900 --> 01:46:14,600
It was the man.

1007
01:46:16,000 --> 01:46:19,700
He's a good man. A true priest.

1008
01:46:23,600 --> 01:46:25,800
He can change things.

1009
01:46:27,900 --> 01:46:29,900
Michael...

1010
01:46:31,000 --> 01:46:34,600
You know, sometimes I think
of poor Fredo.

1011
01:46:35,800 --> 01:46:39,500
Drowned. It was God's will.

1012
01:46:41,800 --> 01:46:44,200
It was a terrible accident.

1013
01:46:45,200 --> 01:46:47,400
But it's finished.

1014
01:46:52,400 --> 01:46:54,700
Michael, I love you.

1015
01:46:56,600 --> 01:46:58,900
I'll always help you.

1016
01:47:10,900 --> 01:47:12,900
Oh, Connie...

1017
01:47:42,400 --> 01:47:48,900
I'm very honoured, Don Altobello, that
you've come from Palermo to visit me.

1018
01:47:52,600 --> 01:47:57,200
The little kid! He's grown.

1019
01:47:58,500 --> 01:48:00,100
Do the donkey.

1020
01:48:02,500 --> 01:48:04,600
(HE BRAYS)

1021
01:48:17,500 --> 01:48:22,200
It's been some time
since we did business together.

1022
01:48:25,300 --> 01:48:29,700
You are my "ace in the hole",
as we say in America.

1023
01:48:30,800 --> 01:48:36,700
I have a stone in my shoe.
You can remove it.

1024
01:48:43,900 --> 01:48:46,300
Only one stone?

1025
01:48:48,800 --> 01:48:52,000
It's a dangerous job.

1026
01:48:52,300 --> 01:48:54,600
A famous man.

1027
01:48:54,800 --> 01:48:57,900
You will have to take precautions.

1028
01:49:01,100 --> 01:49:06,100
Tell me what you want me to do
and I will tell you my price.

1029
01:49:11,200 --> 01:49:13,600
What bread!

1030
01:49:18,000 --> 01:49:20,000
Olive oil...

1031
01:49:25,300 --> 01:49:28,900
Virgin. Only in Sicily.

1032
01:49:31,500 --> 01:49:33,000
Alla salute!

1033
01:49:33,200 --> 01:49:34,900
To his death.

1034
01:49:38,100 --> 01:49:41,600
(TANNO Y ANNOUNCEMENT
IN SICILIAN)

1035
01:49:48,700 --> 01:49:50,400
Kay!

1036
01:49:50,600 --> 01:49:52,700
- Connie!
- How are you?

1037
01:49:53,000 --> 01:49:55,900
Mary, I've missed you.

1038
01:49:56,600 --> 01:50:00,600
- Hello, Michael.
- Mom, look at this.

1039
01:50:04,300 --> 01:50:10,000
- It's too bad Douglas couldn't come.
- I know. He had a very important trial.

1040
01:50:10,400 --> 01:50:13,000
I know he wanted to come.

1041
01:50:13,500 --> 01:50:15,500
- The car is...
- OK.

1042
01:50:17,500 --> 01:50:23,700
- Well, your son is an artist.
- Oh, yes. Thanks to you.

1043
01:50:24,100 --> 01:50:28,700
- What for?
- For making me let him go.

1044
01:50:29,400 --> 01:50:34,200
Well, after all these years,
here I am in Sicily for the first time.

1045
01:50:34,600 --> 01:50:37,800
- I want to get a picture of you together.
- OK.

1046
01:50:39,800 --> 01:50:41,800
Hey, Dad. Smile!

1047
01:50:46,100 --> 01:50:49,800
I see you still have Al Neri. Why?

1048
01:50:50,100 --> 01:50:54,500
I need him. He helps me
get in and out of the car.

1049
01:50:54,800 --> 01:50:58,800
- He carries my briefcase.
- You're still a liar, Michael.

1050
01:50:59,900 --> 01:51:05,800
Let me show you Sicily, the real Sicily.
So you'll understand the family history.

1051
01:51:06,300 --> 01:51:09,300
I think I understand it more than enough.

1052
01:52:00,800 --> 01:52:06,400
Anthony, I have something you made
for me a very long time ago.

1053
01:52:08,600 --> 01:52:11,500
- Might bring you luck.
- Thanks.

1054
01:52:15,300 --> 01:52:18,400
You saved it... I remember.

1055
01:52:22,700 --> 01:52:24,700
Thank you, Dad.

1056
01:52:26,200 --> 01:52:27,700
I'm proud of you.

1057
01:52:28,600 --> 01:52:30,400
Thank you.

1058
01:52:46,300 --> 01:52:48,900
- Are they as good as they look?
- Better.

1059
01:52:49,100 --> 01:52:53,700
They're the best. As long as they are
around, Uncle Michael is safe.

1060
01:52:54,000 --> 01:52:56,300
Goodbye.

1061
01:52:58,400 --> 01:53:01,700
- Tell your father I'll be back for dinner.
- OK.

1062
01:53:01,900 --> 01:53:04,400
- Have fun.
- Tell Tony to wait for me.

1063
01:53:04,700 --> 01:53:06,700
I will.

1064
01:53:08,700 --> 01:53:11,800
Buongiorno, signora. At your service.

1065
01:53:16,200 --> 01:53:19,600
If I see Dad, I'll tell him you left.

1066
01:53:24,700 --> 01:53:28,300
You're the only one left
with my father's strength.

1067
01:53:30,700 --> 01:53:35,000
If anything happens to Michael,
I want you to strike back.

1068
01:53:37,600 --> 01:53:39,300
I'll have everything ready.

1069
01:53:43,100 --> 01:53:45,700
Do you swear?

1070
01:53:52,100 --> 01:53:54,500
I swear to you.

1071
01:54:24,400 --> 01:54:26,600
Here it is.

1072
01:54:27,700 --> 01:54:30,700
The house where my father was born.

1073
01:54:31,400 --> 01:54:36,900
This is where they came to take him
when he was a boy. To kill him.

1074
01:54:40,200 --> 01:54:41,800
Wait...

1075
01:54:42,600 --> 01:54:44,600
Listen to that.

1076
01:55:03,800 --> 01:55:06,700
You know Mary's in love.

1077
01:55:07,200 --> 01:55:09,500
Yes, I know.

1078
01:55:09,800 --> 01:55:13,900
With a handsome young Italian man
with dark eyes...

1079
01:55:15,400 --> 01:55:17,500
I won't allow it.

1080
01:55:19,900 --> 01:55:23,500
It's wrong. It's wrong and it's dangerous.

1081
01:55:24,000 --> 01:55:26,700
"Oh, father, my father!"

1082
01:55:27,300 --> 01:55:29,800
"Give me time to pray to the Lord."

1083
01:55:30,000 --> 01:55:37,100
When the Baron found out that his
daughter had betrayed her husband...

1084
01:55:37,600 --> 01:55:38,900
"No forgiveness!"

1085
01:55:39,100 --> 01:55:44,200
Her father lifted his sword...
and stabbed her through the heart.

1086
01:55:55,800 --> 01:55:57,700
Honour, huh?

1087
01:56:16,700 --> 01:56:19,700
I remember the time you came
to my parents' house

1088
01:56:19,900 --> 01:56:23,300
and told me about the family business.

1089
01:56:23,600 --> 01:56:29,000
How you'd never have anything
to do with it. You sounded like Tony.

1090
01:56:29,700 --> 01:56:32,700
I was a lot like Tony.

1091
01:56:39,300 --> 01:56:42,100
- I can barely see him... Kay?
- What?

1092
01:56:42,400 --> 01:56:44,700
- Do you mind driving?
- What's wrong?

1093
01:56:45,000 --> 01:56:48,000
My eyes. Sometimes
they're all right, but...

1094
01:56:49,600 --> 01:56:52,300
I have to see Don Tommasino...

1095
01:56:55,600 --> 01:56:57,600
Well...

1096
01:56:58,100 --> 01:57:01,800
- There are no bodyguards today.
- I really snuck away.

1097
01:57:09,000 --> 01:57:13,300
Father, where are you going?
Would you like a ride?

1098
01:57:23,000 --> 01:57:26,800
I know you. You're Mosca
from Montelepre.

1099
01:57:28,100 --> 01:57:31,800
You were an assassin then
and you're an assassin now.

1100
01:57:32,200 --> 01:57:35,400
I know Michael Corleone
is at your house.

1101
01:57:35,900 --> 01:57:38,800
I will pass through the gates with you.

1102
01:57:54,800 --> 01:57:56,400
How are you?

1103
01:57:56,600 --> 01:58:00,600
This is Calo, one of my bodyguards
in the old days.

1104
01:58:05,700 --> 01:58:08,500
- We can wait here.
- You want a drink?

1105
01:58:13,900 --> 01:58:16,900
I spent a lot of time in this room...

1106
01:58:17,900 --> 01:58:19,900
...thinking of you.

1107
01:58:23,200 --> 01:58:25,800
And then you got married.

1108
01:58:29,100 --> 01:58:32,800
- I still thought of you.
- What's in that room?

1109
01:58:36,900 --> 01:58:40,900
This is dangerous for you. This is Sicily.

1110
01:58:43,600 --> 01:58:46,700
- I love this country.
- Why?

1111
01:58:48,600 --> 01:58:54,400
Well, all through history, terrible things
have happened to these people.

1112
01:58:55,400 --> 01:58:57,900
Terrible injustices.

1113
01:58:58,700 --> 01:59:03,700
But they still expect good,
rather than bad, will happen to them.

1114
01:59:04,100 --> 01:59:06,900
Sort of like me and you?

1115
01:59:10,300 --> 01:59:13,700
- How so?
- I'm still here, right?

1116
01:59:13,900 --> 01:59:17,000
We do have a bad history,
but I'm still here.

1117
01:59:17,300 --> 01:59:19,800
Yes, you are, but with dread.

1118
01:59:24,800 --> 01:59:26,400
Give me the order!

1119
01:59:26,900 --> 01:59:30,500
Is that supposed to make me
not dread you?

1120
01:59:32,600 --> 01:59:35,200
We're in Sicily. It's opera.

1121
01:59:37,100 --> 01:59:39,100
OK.

1122
01:59:41,000 --> 01:59:43,300
What do we do now?

1123
01:59:46,000 --> 01:59:50,600
Be reasonable.
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1124
01:59:57,200 --> 02:00:00,000
I want you to forgive me.

1125
02:00:02,400 --> 02:00:05,400
- For what?
- Everything.

1126
02:00:09,000 --> 02:00:11,900
Oh, like God?

1127
02:00:12,600 --> 02:00:15,600
No, I need something a little closer.

1128
02:00:18,600 --> 02:00:21,700
You couldn't understand,
back in those days.

1129
02:00:23,200 --> 02:00:27,900
I loved my father. I swore I would
never be a man like him,

1130
02:00:28,300 --> 02:00:32,400
but I loved him and he was in danger.
What could I do?

1131
02:00:32,700 --> 02:00:36,000
And then later, you were in danger.

1132
02:00:36,400 --> 02:00:40,200
Our children were in danger.
What could I do?

1133
02:00:40,400 --> 02:00:45,900
You were all that I...
Ioved and valued most in the world.

1134
02:00:47,900 --> 02:00:50,400
Now I'm losing you. I lost you.

1135
02:00:51,400 --> 02:00:53,500
You're gone.

1136
02:00:54,500 --> 02:00:58,100
And it was all for nothing. So...

1137
02:01:02,300 --> 02:01:07,200
You have to understand,
I had a whole different destiny planned.

1138
02:01:10,600 --> 02:01:13,200
All right, I'll stop.

1139
02:01:23,100 --> 02:01:27,000
I really don't know what you
want from me, Michael.

1140
02:01:27,400 --> 02:01:32,200
- I mean...
- I'm not the man that you think I am.

1141
02:01:33,700 --> 02:01:37,600
- I don't know.
- I love you, Kay.

1142
02:01:39,000 --> 02:01:41,700
Don't dread me any more.

1143
02:01:46,900 --> 02:01:50,700
You know, every night here in Sicily...

1144
02:01:52,900 --> 02:01:58,100
...I dream about my wife
and my children...

1145
02:02:01,700 --> 02:02:03,900
...and how I lost them.

1146
02:02:05,600 --> 02:02:11,100
I guess that if it's any consolation,
I want you to know that...

1147
02:02:14,700 --> 02:02:16,000
...that...

1148
02:02:17,200 --> 02:02:19,900
...I always loved you, Michael.

1149
02:02:21,200 --> 02:02:23,000
And you know...

1150
02:02:24,600 --> 02:02:27,200
...always, I always will.

1151
02:02:42,700 --> 02:02:44,200
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

1152
02:02:55,000 --> 02:02:56,800
What is it?

1153
02:02:58,200 --> 02:03:01,200
Don Tommasino. He's been found shot.

1154
02:03:02,600 --> 02:03:04,000
Dead?

1155
02:03:06,200 --> 02:03:09,800
My master is dead.
Blood calls for blood.

1156
02:03:10,400 --> 02:03:13,600
I must revenge him in some way!

1157
02:03:16,600 --> 02:03:21,900
Some day you may have to do
a difficult service for me.

1158
02:03:22,700 --> 02:03:25,200
Command me, tell me what to do!

1159
02:03:25,700 --> 02:03:27,000
It never ends.

1160
02:03:27,300 --> 02:03:29,600
I will avenge him!

1161
02:03:44,700 --> 02:03:46,300
Totals...

1162
02:03:48,000 --> 02:03:50,800
Lorscheider, 1 vote.

1163
02:03:51,300 --> 02:03:54,100
Siri, 11 votes.

1164
02:03:54,900 --> 02:03:58,700
Lamberto, 99 votes.

1165
02:04:03,800 --> 02:04:09,200
Do you accept your election
as Supreme Pontiff?

1166
02:04:09,500 --> 02:04:15,100
Oh, God, shed light on the decision
they have taken on my behalf.

1167
02:04:16,400 --> 02:04:17,900
I accept.

1168
02:04:18,100 --> 02:04:20,600
What name will you choose?

1169
02:04:20,900 --> 02:04:23,800
John Paul the First.

1170
02:04:49,400 --> 02:04:52,500
(LOUDSPEAKER ANNOUNCEMENT
IN ITALIAN)

1171
02:04:53,400 --> 02:04:58,900
I will do things "right away",
rather than in "a little while".

1172
02:05:00,500 --> 02:05:03,800
(RADIO) Frederick Keinszig
known as "God's Banker",

1173
02:05:04,100 --> 02:05:05,700
has been reported missing.

1174
02:05:05,900 --> 02:05:12,400
He was last seen leaving the Rome
offices of Vatican owned lmmobiliare.

1175
02:05:13,300 --> 02:05:17,100
Also missing was a large sum
of money and several documents.

1176
02:05:18,300 --> 02:05:20,900
Keinszig, you fool.

1177
02:05:23,600 --> 02:05:28,400
His absence casts further suspicion
on the dealings of the Vatican Bank.

1178
02:05:28,800 --> 02:05:31,500
For several years,
the bank and its companies

1179
02:05:31,900 --> 02:05:36,300
have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practices.

1180
02:05:37,100 --> 02:05:41,200
Lucchesi, will you please
try to understand?

1181
02:05:42,500 --> 02:05:47,100
I have phoned him.
I have waited here by the phone.

1182
02:05:49,800 --> 02:05:54,200
You would do well to remember,
Mr Lucchesi,

1183
02:05:54,600 --> 02:06:01,300
that this Pope has very different ideas
from the last one.

1184
02:06:23,200 --> 02:06:25,400
Goodbye, my old friend.

1185
02:06:27,700 --> 02:06:31,000
You could have lived a little longer.

1186
02:06:31,400 --> 02:06:34,600
I could be closer to my dream.

1187
02:06:39,800 --> 02:06:43,100
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1188
02:06:47,700 --> 02:06:51,500
Why was I so feared,
and you so loved?

1189
02:06:52,700 --> 02:06:54,800
What was it?

1190
02:06:55,300 --> 02:06:58,100
I was no less honourable.

1191
02:06:59,400 --> 02:07:01,700
I wanted to do good.

1192
02:07:05,600 --> 02:07:08,900
What betrayed me?
My mind? My heart?

1193
02:07:11,600 --> 02:07:14,300
Why do I condemn myself so?

1194
02:07:20,600 --> 02:07:22,700
I swear,

1195
02:07:22,900 --> 02:07:25,600
on the lives of my children...

1196
02:07:29,700 --> 02:07:32,600
Give me a chance to redeem myself...

1197
02:07:36,300 --> 02:07:39,900
...and I will sin no more.

1198
02:08:03,900 --> 02:08:08,000
You look pale. Bad news?
Tell me right away.

1199
02:08:10,100 --> 02:08:13,400
It's not just a bad banking deal.

1200
02:08:13,700 --> 02:08:16,700
These guys are butchers.

1201
02:08:16,900 --> 02:08:20,000
- What guys?
- Lucchesi.

1202
02:08:21,400 --> 02:08:25,600
He controls all of them:
Altobello, the Archbishop...

1203
02:08:26,900 --> 02:08:29,500
...others higher up, P2 maybe.

1204
02:08:29,700 --> 02:08:33,500
Secret unknown.
They're running things.

1205
02:08:36,700 --> 02:08:41,700
- I'm in their way.
- He's hired an assassin to kill you.

1206
02:08:42,100 --> 02:08:45,400
A Sicilian. I don't know his name.

1207
02:08:46,800 --> 02:08:49,200
But they say he never fails.

1208
02:08:50,400 --> 02:08:52,800
Then no one is safe.

1209
02:08:55,300 --> 02:08:58,500
Even the new Pope is in danger.

1210
02:08:58,800 --> 02:09:02,600
We still have time. We can prevent this.

1211
02:09:07,000 --> 02:09:09,700
I tried, Vincent.

1212
02:09:11,600 --> 02:09:14,400
I tried...

1213
02:09:14,700 --> 02:09:20,100
...to keep everything from coming
to this. But it's not possible.

1214
02:09:20,400 --> 02:09:22,800
Not in this world.

1215
02:09:23,900 --> 02:09:25,800
Give me the order.

1216
02:09:29,400 --> 02:09:32,400
You won't be able to go back.

1217
02:09:32,700 --> 02:09:35,700
- You'll be like me.
- Good.

1218
02:09:36,700 --> 02:09:39,200
All my life I wanted out.

1219
02:09:39,500 --> 02:09:42,200
I wanted the family out.

1220
02:09:43,600 --> 02:09:45,200
I don't want out.

1221
02:09:45,900 --> 02:09:49,000
I want the power to preserve the family.

1222
02:09:53,300 --> 02:09:55,700
I'm asking for the order.

1223
02:10:16,500 --> 02:10:18,600
It's done.

1224
02:10:19,700 --> 02:10:22,400
Because I can't do it any more.

1225
02:10:25,700 --> 02:10:29,600
Well, it doesn't matter.
Vincent knows what to do.

1226
02:10:29,800 --> 02:10:34,700
Come on outside.
Take a rest and don't think about it.

1227
02:10:35,100 --> 02:10:39,000
- All I do is think about it.
- I'm your son.

1228
02:10:39,400 --> 02:10:42,100
Command me in all things.

1229
02:10:43,700 --> 02:10:46,300
Give up my daughter.

1230
02:10:48,800 --> 02:10:51,800
That's the price you pay...

1231
02:10:52,100 --> 02:10:54,700
...for the life you choose.

1232
02:11:20,300 --> 02:11:22,100
Nephew...

1233
02:11:24,400 --> 02:11:26,700
...from this moment on...

1234
02:11:28,100 --> 02:11:31,000
...call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1235
02:11:35,200 --> 02:11:36,800
Sit.

1236
02:11:51,700 --> 02:11:53,700
Don Vincenzo...

1237
02:11:59,500 --> 02:12:01,200
Don Corleone...

1238
02:12:04,400 --> 02:12:07,000
Don Vincenzo Corleone...

1239
02:13:40,400 --> 02:13:41,700
E tu, Vincenzo...

1240
02:13:42,800 --> 02:13:47,500
I know how you feel about Michael,
but you can't save him.

1241
02:13:48,400 --> 02:13:50,100
He's lost.

1242
02:13:51,400 --> 02:13:52,900
Think of yourself.

1243
02:13:54,400 --> 02:13:57,100
What's your answer, Vincent?

1244
02:13:58,700 --> 02:14:01,300
Enjoy the opera.

1245
02:14:02,700 --> 02:14:05,200
It's all taken care of.

1246
02:14:10,000 --> 02:14:12,800
Check the bar. I'll check the top floor.

1247
02:14:16,700 --> 02:14:20,800
"Here's hoping Tony sings better at the
Teatro Massimo than in the shower.

1248
02:14:21,200 --> 02:14:23,100
"Love, Douglas."

1249
02:14:23,400 --> 02:14:26,900
- My darling Constanza!
- Don Altobello.

1250
02:14:27,900 --> 02:14:31,400
- This is a great occasion.
- Come, sit down.

1251
02:14:35,400 --> 02:14:39,800
Happy birthday.
You're 80, but don't look more than 60.

1252
02:14:40,200 --> 02:14:41,800
You're the only one who remembered.

1253
02:14:42,200 --> 02:14:47,400
We've just got the word. The Pope has
ratified the lmmobiliare deal. We've won.

1254
02:14:47,800 --> 02:14:49,800
Congratulations.

1255
02:14:52,200 --> 02:14:54,400
Strange how things work.

1256
02:14:54,600 --> 02:14:59,400
The Pope is doing what you said
he'd do. He's cleaning house.

1257
02:14:59,900 --> 02:15:04,100
He should be careful.
It's dangerous to be an honest man.

1258
02:15:09,900 --> 02:15:14,100
I want to put more muscle backstage
with Tony.

1259
02:15:24,900 --> 02:15:28,200
On your birthday you used to
shower me with treats.

1260
02:15:28,500 --> 02:15:30,800
Tootsie Rolls!

1261
02:15:31,100 --> 02:15:36,400
The nuns who made this cannoli took a
vow of silence. They're the very finest.

1262
02:15:40,300 --> 02:15:43,400
- Hey.
- Hey, cuz.

1263
02:15:45,100 --> 02:15:48,200
Hi. Where's your leather?

1264
02:15:52,000 --> 02:15:53,400
Stop it.

1265
02:15:59,400 --> 02:16:02,700
You're so thin. You eat it.

1266
02:16:19,400 --> 02:16:20,700
 buono.

1267
02:16:21,400 --> 02:16:23,700
Grazie!

1268
02:16:26,600 --> 02:16:30,700
It's over. There are things I have to do
that you can't be part of.

1269
02:16:31,000 --> 02:16:34,000
It's not your father's decision, it's mine.

1270
02:16:35,700 --> 02:16:38,200
Don't hate your father.

1271
02:16:39,900 --> 02:16:43,600
There are things I'll be part of
that you can't be around.

1272
02:16:45,800 --> 02:16:49,200
After tonight,
you won't see me any more.

1273
02:16:52,900 --> 02:16:56,900
You've got to understand, Mary.
You've got to understand.

1274
02:16:57,600 --> 02:17:00,100
I'll always love you.

1275
02:17:12,500 --> 02:17:13,900
Love somebody else.

1276
02:18:08,200 --> 02:18:10,700
(TONY SINGS IN ITALIAN)

1277
02:20:55,300 --> 02:20:59,200
- They won't try anything.
- Everything's fine. It's all clear.

1278
02:20:59,600 --> 02:21:02,500
I've already sent Al Neri to the Vatican.

1279
02:21:14,500 --> 02:21:18,700
- Is this Mr Lucchesi's house?
- Yes.

1280
02:21:18,900 --> 02:21:22,900
I have a message
from Michael Corleone.

1281
02:21:24,600 --> 02:21:26,600
Let him in.

1282
02:22:55,100 --> 02:22:56,700
Buona sera.

1283
02:26:18,000 --> 02:26:20,600
Good. You got him.

1284
02:27:12,200 --> 02:27:15,600
(VINCENT) Tonight the Corleone famil
settles its accounts.

1285
02:27:15,900 --> 02:27:20,400
Keinszig...
That little Swiss banker fuck.

1286
02:27:21,800 --> 02:27:26,200
He's been swindling everyone
from the beginning. Fuck him.

1287
02:27:27,200 --> 02:27:29,800
Don Lucchesi, my friend.

1288
02:27:30,100 --> 02:27:33,000
Calo will pay him a visit at his home.

1289
02:27:35,200 --> 02:27:38,500
Neri, take a train to Rome.

1290
02:27:40,200 --> 02:27:42,100
Light a candle for the Archbishop.

1291
02:28:18,500 --> 02:28:21,800
Tea, Your Holiness? It helps you sleep.

1292
02:28:44,400 --> 02:28:47,200
This is from Vincent Corleone!

1293
02:29:45,600 --> 02:29:50,200
It's serious. Our man inside the Vatican
says there's a plot against the Pope.

1294
02:29:50,700 --> 02:29:52,800
He'll have a heart attack?

1295
02:29:59,900 --> 02:30:04,900
This Pope has powerful enemies.
We may not be in time to save him.

1296
02:30:08,000 --> 02:30:09,600
Let's go back.

1297
02:30:39,900 --> 02:30:41,600
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

1298
02:30:51,700 --> 02:30:54,000
Eminenza...

1299
02:31:02,200 --> 02:31:04,300
The Holy Father is dead!

1300
02:32:34,100 --> 02:32:35,500
Sleep.

1301
02:32:36,800 --> 02:32:39,200
Sleep, Godfather.

1302
02:33:49,000 --> 02:33:51,000
Speak to me.

1303
02:33:51,300 --> 02:33:58,200
I'm here to tell you that you have lost
the faith of the people.

1304
02:34:00,600 --> 02:34:04,300
He who builds on the people,
builds on mud.

1305
02:34:04,800 --> 02:34:08,800
And Michael Corleone's message?

1306
02:34:26,100 --> 02:34:31,900
It's very important.
I must whisper it in your ear.

1307
02:34:36,100 --> 02:34:37,900
He's clean.

1308
02:34:56,000 --> 02:34:58,900
Power wears out those
who don't have it.

1309
02:35:25,200 --> 02:35:28,200
(MUSIC BUILDS TO A CLIMAX)

1310
02:35:41,400 --> 02:35:43,800
(MUSIC ENDS)

1311
02:36:27,600 --> 02:36:30,800
- I like this outfit.
- I figured you would.

1312
02:36:31,000 --> 02:36:32,700
Say hello.

1313
02:36:54,900 --> 02:36:58,600
- Can I talk to you now?
- No, it's not a good time.

1314
02:36:59,000 --> 02:37:02,800
- You're just like my father.
- Stay with the family. Go on.

1315
02:37:04,200 --> 02:37:06,000
- Talk to me.
- The twins are dead.

1316
02:37:06,100 --> 02:37:10,900
In about one minute, there will be
carabinieri all over this place.

1317
02:37:11,300 --> 02:37:13,800
Get everybody to the cars, quietly.

1318
02:37:14,100 --> 02:37:16,500
- Got it.
- Quiet.

1319
02:37:30,500 --> 02:37:33,400
The name Corleone
will be associated with a voice.

1320
02:37:43,600 --> 02:37:45,200
Dad...

1321
02:38:04,600 --> 02:38:07,900
Dad... Why are you doing this to me?

1322
02:38:17,400 --> 02:38:20,200
Move back, move back.

1323
02:38:20,700 --> 02:38:25,900
- You don't have to do this to me.
- Do what? What do you mean?

1324
02:38:52,100 --> 02:38:54,100
Dad...

1325
02:39:10,200 --> 02:39:12,800
No! Mary!

1326
02:39:15,800 --> 02:39:18,100
God, no! No! No!

1327
02:39:22,800 --> 02:39:25,000
(FAY WAILS)

1328
02:39:53,000 --> 02:39:55,500
(SCREAMS SILENTLY)

1329
02:40:17,000 --> 02:40:19,800
(AGONISED SCREAM)

